title: velvet waffles
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks; add milk and oil.
Pour into flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold into egg whites lightly, but thoroughly.
Use 1/2 cup batter for each waffle.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Serve with fruits:
apples, pineapple, bananas or other fruits.

title: barbecued wieners
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and mustard.
Add pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
You can add Tabasco sauce to spice it up, but add a little more cornstarch to thicken the sauce.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Dissolve jello with water; add berries.
Refrigerate until thick.
Pour over pieces slowly.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Line lettuce leaves in large bowl, letting edges show.
In another bowl, mix apples, grapes, cherries, nuts, marshmallows and celery.
In a small bowl, blend Miracle Whip and sugar, then add Cool Whip.
Pour dressing mixture in with fruit and fold in well. Pour into large leaf-lined bowl.
Place leaf and orange twist in center for garnish.

title: mild salsa
directions: Mix altogether.
You may want more or less of a particular ingredient.
Cook it down for a few hours or until consistency you prefer.
Stir occasionally.
Put in hot pint jars and seal.
This is mild at first, but as it sits on the shelf, it gets hotter. Makes 10 pints.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Add onions, pepper and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt.
Cover with crushed ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Don't wash.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat just to a boil. Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: grandma ann's goulash
directions: In a 6-quart pot (or larger), add water, tomatoes, ground beef, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil.
Let simmer 1 hour.
Then add 1/2 cup rice, noodles, potatoes and allspice.
Cook 1/2 hour longer, then last, add diced green pepper.
Cook goulash until pepper is tender.
Cooking time:
1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine apples with all ingredients except butter.
Pour into pie crust lining.
Dot with butter.
Moisten edges with cold water.
Cover with top crust.
Press firmly together.
Prick top with a fork.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 40 or 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cake(serves 24)
directions: Sift salt, flour and sugar twice in bowl.
Bring oleo, cocoa and coffee to a rapid boil and pour over flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into greased jelly roll pan, 16 x 11-inch.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato soup
directions: In saucepan, sift the flour gradually into the oil, mixing with each addition until smooth.
Add the milk and cook over low heat until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Add the grated onion, paprika, celery salt and pepper, mixing well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion together in about 1 tablespoon butter or margarine until tender (but still firm).
In a large bowl, combine chicken, chestnuts, soup, celery and onion, rice and soy sauce.
Top with corn flakes.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Dip chicken into eggs, then into bread crumbs to coat.
In a skillet on medium heat, add oleo.
When melted, place chicken in skillet and brown on both sides, then add sauce.
Lower flame and cover for 10 minutes.
Then sprinkle cheese and parsley on top and cook another 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Makes 4 servings.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, sugar, salt, soda, bananas, oleo, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Wilt tortillas in chicken broth from boned chicken and line a large casserole with tortillas.
Place boned chicken on them. Cook onion an pepper in 1/2 c broth until
tender.
Add soup, tomatoes, and chili powder.
Mix and pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese and heat just long enough to melt cheese.
If you like it hooter, you can add a jalapeno pepper.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla in a medium bowl; beat well. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in chocolate morsels, pecans and coconut.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
1 (9-inch) pie.

title: congealed salad (pink)
directions: Mix juice from pineapple and add enough water to make 4 cups. Add marshmallows and jello to liquid and melt over low heat; stir until marshmallows are dissolved.
Cool and let thicken slightly. Mix cream cheese, pineapple and nuts and add to thickened mixture.

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: Combine ground chuck and onion in large skillet.
Cook until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Serve over hamburger buns.

title: carrot bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients separately.
In a large bowl, beat eggs. Add all-bran, oil, sugar and molasses.
Add dry ingredients, carrots and raisins.
Spoon into greased muffin cups and bake at 350° to 20 to 25 minutes until brown on top.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save pineapple juice.
Combine water, sugar, soy sauce, vinegar and pineapple juice.
Set aside.
Combine flour, salt and garlic.
Mix pork in flour mixture.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add pork; brown on all sides.
Add 1 cup of liquid mixture and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 hour in covered skillet. Uncover; add remaining liquid and continue heating.
Add pineapple chunks, bell pepper, carrots and tomato.
Mix carefully and cook until vegetables are heated, 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chinese salad
directions: Mix together in a large bowl lettuce,
spinach, onions, almonds and sesame seed.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together. Roll about 1/4-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Press pecan half into circles and bake in hot oven at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: orange-lemon frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: stuffing balls
directions: Saute celery, onions and seasonings in the margarine in skillet for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Shape into 12 balls and put one in each of 12 well-greased muffin pan sections.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken, in bowl.
Dip chicken pieces in mixture and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend well with other ingredients. Chill.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Grease 9 x 12 casserole pan.
Wash and slice strawberries and rhubarb, place on bottom of pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and drop cake mixture by the spoonful on top of strawberries and rhubarb. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: herb bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
At 1-inch intervals, make diagonal cuts in bread; do not cut through bottom.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients until well blended.
Spread mixture between slices and over top.
Wrap bread completely in foil.
Bake 20 minutes until spread is melted and bread is hot and crusty.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: pigs in a blanket casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and place in the bottom of greased baking dish. Brown ground beef lightly with onion, salt and pepper.
Mix meat and raw rice and spread over cabbage.
Cover with tomato soup and water.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients for 2 minutes.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Bake at 350° in tube pan for about 50 minutes or until done.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Marinate at least one hour.
Pour off marinade and reserve.
Bake chicken at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and baste with marinade. Continue baking 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and richly glazed, basting frequently.
Makes 6 servings.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots.
Place in a saucepan and cover with water. Simmer until just tender.
Drain.
Transfer to a glass bowl, add sliced onions and green peppers.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over the vegetables.
Cover and marinate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cheese, confectioners sugar and egg until well blended.
Pour over graham cracker mixture.
Slice bananas in half lengthwise; place on cream cheese mixture.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over mixture; sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Chill.

title: oven roast hamburgers
directions: Mix together all ingredients and add to beef.
Shape into 50 patties.
Place in greased pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hawaiian cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Add coconut and pineapple, then mix in the dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Set out pie shell and strawberries.
Set aside 2 cups whole berries.
Crush remaining berries with fork and set aside.

Mix sugar, cornstarch and milk or water in a saucepan in order, stirring gently and constantly, bringing to a rapid boil and cook for 3 minutes or until mixture is clear (mixture should be clear if used water).
Stir in crushed berries and blend in lemon juice and food coloring.
Cool mixture slightly with pan set in bowl of ice and water.
Cover and set aside.
Beat together cream cheese and orange juice until blended.
Spread over bottom of pie shell; cover with whole berries.
Pour cooled strawberry mixture over berries.
Chill in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Top with sweetened whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 7-up strawberry pie
directions: Cook first five ingredients until thick and clear.
Let cool. Slice 1 quart of strawberries into cooled 9-inch crust. Pour gelatin mixture over strawberries.

title: two potato salad with dill dressing(healthy recipe)
directions: Mix yogurt, mayo, dill weed, mustard and salt in a large glass or plastic bowl.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate about 4 hours or until chilled.
Yields 4 servings, about 1 cup each.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar together.
Press in ungreased square pan; bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Pour over hot crust.
Bake until no indentation remains when touched lightly in center, about 25 minutes.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: bonnie's refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast and dissolve sugar in water.
Add milk (cooled to lukewarm), shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl.
Grease top and cover.
Store in refrigerator. Shape rolls about 2 hours before serving.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in hot oven (400° to 425°) for 15 to 20 minutes. Punch down unused dough and return to refrigerator.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen medium-sized rolls.

title: bookbinder's paste
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water slowly, stirring out lumps. Cook in double boiler over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat when paste begins to thicken.
It thickens as it cools. Keep covered.
Thin with hot water when necessary.

title: old fashioned cabbage rolls
directions: Blend meats, egg, milk and bread crumbs.
Stir in salt, molasses, spices and onion.
Mix well.
Cut out core of cabbage. Separate outer 12 leaves.
Remove thick vein of each leaf.
Drop leaves in boiling water.
Cover; steam 3 minutes or until soft and bright green.
Remove with slotted spoon and reserve liquid. Place meat on leaves.
Fold sides in and roll up.
Fasten with a wooden pick.
Heat butter and brown rolls on all sides.
Transfer to a 3-quart casserole. Mix reserved water from boiling leave with butter and drippings.
Pour over filled rolls.

title: raisin-pecan pie
directions: Roll
pastry
to 1/8 inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Place
in
a 9-inch pie plate; trim off excess pastry along
edges.
Fold
edges
under, and flute.
Prick bottom and sides of
pastry with a fork.
Bake at 450° for 3 to 5 minutes; remove
from oven.
Cool.
Combine butter and sugar in a saucepan; cook
over
low
heat,
stirring
constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook
minutes.
Stir in eggs, vinegar, cinnamon, raisins,
pecans and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for
30 minutes or until pie is set.
When pie has cooled, garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: chef's secret pan coating
directions: Mix all ingredients together really well.
Store at room temperature or refrigerate and warm a few seconds in microwave to soften when ready to use.
Spread on cake pans with a pastry brush.
Eliminates "greasing and flouring".

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter with salt; add sugar and cream well.
Blend in egg and vanilla; add flour and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: irish stew("welsh version")
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in oil until soft.
Add water, meat and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Add vegetables and simmer 1 more hour.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with whole wheat bread, butter and milk to drink.

title: pizza bread
directions: Thaw bread in a buttered dish.
Cover with a towel and rise to double in size.

title: marolyn's crab imperial
directions: Melt butter and mix in flour.
Add milk, stirring constantly. Cook until thickened.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread.
Cool.
Fold in mayo, lemon, salt and pepper.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons butter; saute crab and mix with cooled mixture.
Put in shells; sprinkle with paprika and bake at 450° until hot, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna noodle supreme
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
In large bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, milk and mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add hot pasta, tuna, Sea Sticks, broccoli, green onion and red peppers. Stir until blended.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Blend all but coconut together in blender for 3 minutes. Butter and flour a 10-inch glass pie plate (this is a must).
Pour liquid into plate.
Top with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Add a little milk
if needed to make thinner.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Cook
butter, oleo and sugar for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla. Place
crackers
on
cookie sheet with sides touching and pour above
mixture
over them.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Put on waxed paper immediately.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup and bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Mix in peanut butter; then mix in Rice Krispies.
Press mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in microwave. Mix together and spread on Rice Krispie mixture.

title: apple betty pie
directions: Put apples in 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle on orange juice.
Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter.
Sprinkle topping over apples. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipping cream.

title: flounder fillets in foil
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in wine, lemon juice and parsley.
Cook until most of liquid evaporates.
Place each fillet on a lightly buttered piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Season with pepper and spoon mushroom sauce over each fillet.
Seal foil together.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, syrup and butter.
Spread peanuts in pie shell.
Pour filling over top.
Bake in a preheated moderate oven (325°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool before cutting.
Makes one 8-inch pie.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Mix warm water and yeast until yeast dissolves.
Add sugar, salt, oil and milk.
Add 4 cups of flour (add more, up to 4 1/2 cups as needed).
Fill 2 well-greased coffee cans half full.
Set plastic tops on cans while dough rises.
When dough reaches tops, about 1 hour, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from cans.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces.
Season with salt and pepper. Place in crock-pot.
Add prepared vegetables.
Cover with tomatoes.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: clam dip
directions: Cream all ingredients.
Use clam liquid to thin.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine first 3 ingredients and beat well. Add milk, corn and salt; stir until mixed. Melt butter in a casserole dish in the oven. When butter is melted, add mixture. Return to the oven and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until brown.

title: mud hen cookies
directions: Mix butter, white sugar, egg yolks, soda, vanilla and flour; spread lightly on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle nuts on top; press down. Beat egg whites stiff; add brown sugar.
Pour over batter.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 to 35 minutes.
Use 13 x 9 1/2-inch baking pan.

title: creamed crabmeat with artichoke hearts
directions: Cook first three ingredients in 1 tablespoon butter in a heavy saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender. Drain.
Press mushroom mixture, crabmeat and artichoke hearts between paper towels to remove excess moisture and set aside.

title: rocky road cake
directions: Grease and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan or Bundt pan.
In small bowl, mix walnuts, raisins, marshmallows and chocolate pieces.
In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat together cake mix, eggs, mayonnaise and water just until blended.
Increase speed to medium; beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in nut mixture.
Pour in prepared pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Remove.
Cool on rack.
If desired, dust with confectioners sugar. Makes 12 servings.

title: pineapple ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and canned milk very good.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in freezer and fill to line with milk.
Now get busy.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place the cut up chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan to bake.
Mix other ingredients together and bring to boiling point.
Pour over chicken; bake for 1 hour or more.
Baste sauce over chicken 2 or 3 times.
You may add parsley flakes or garlic to the sauce, if desired.

title: red spicy applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in the cup of hot water (microwave on Medium-high).
Add jello and last applesauce.
Pour in mold.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and soda to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and nuts.
Beat until creamy and drop on wax paper over which salt has been sprinkled.
Use a large pan because it foams quite a bit.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In saucepan, melt and heat to boiling the butter, cocoa, shortening and water. In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Combine and mix with cocoa mixture.
In a small bowl, combine the eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Combine and mix well with the other ingredients. Pour into greased 13 x 11-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Leave cake in pan. Cover with icing after removing cake from oven.

title: vegetarian wiener dish
directions: Slice each frank into 3 parts.
Fry in frying pan with oil, barbecue sauce and soy sauce for about 10 minutes, or until lightly crispy.
Add beans, onion, puree, cayenne and flour.
Stir and simmer on low.
Pour onto serving dish and sprinkle cheese over top.
May be served with corn chips or corn bread.

title: banana cake
directions: Sour milk:
1 tablespoon of vinegar to 1/2 cup homo milk and set aside for a few minutes.

title: lemon blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 12 cup muffin tin or line tin with cupcake liners.

title: dirt "dessert"
directions: You will need a clean, hard plastic flowerpot, fake flowers, candy (gummi worms) and wax paper.

title: microwave peanut brittle(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, peanuts and salt in a large casserole dish. Stir well. Microwave on High for 11 minutes. Mixture will be light brown. Add butter and vanilla. Stir well. Microwave on High for 6 minutes or until mixture reaches hard-crack stage. Stir in soda quickly. Pour into large flat pan to cool. Be sure to grease pan. Let stand at least 1 hour. Break into pieces.

title: black forest cake
directions: Place marshmallows in greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Mix cake mix as directed and pour over marshmallows. Pour pie filling over cake mix. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes. When cake is cooled, frost with Cool Whip. This is a very moist cake.

title: crawfish or shrimp etouffee
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add onion, celery, green peppers and garlic. Cook until tender.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, but save 1/4 cup salsa.
Firmly pack mixture into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan; cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil last 5 minutes to brown.
Top with remaining salsa.

title: fiesta pie
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl, stir in milk.
Add remaining ingredients, except salsa and sour cream.
Pour into greased 9-inch microwave pie plate.
Cover loosely with wax paper. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir edges to center and from center to edge.
Microwave 4 minutes or until center isn't wet. Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: veal scaloppine ala marsala
directions: Cut veal into
2-inch
strips.	Flour lightly and brown in olive oil, butter
and salt pork.
Remove salt pork;
brown veal 3 minutes each
side.
Add salt, pepper and wine.
Simmer 5 minutes; add onions, mushrooms, mangos, tomatoes, garlic and parsley. Simmer until tender.
I use my electric skillet.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Line a large dish with meat.
Spread with oregano, garlic, salt, etc. to taste.
Put a layer of onions over this, then potatoes.
Arrange can of tomatoes over top of casserole and sprinkle cheese and seasoning on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Cover first hour and leave the lid off.
Serves 4 large portions.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in greased dish.
Mix flour and sugar together and sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Top with crushed crackers.
Drizzle top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: filled french rolls
directions: Cut up first 4 ingredients and add tomato sauce and butter. Scoop out 1 dozen French rolls and divide the mixture evenly between rolls.
Wrap each roll in foil and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°. In a roasting pan coated with cooking spray, toss potatoes with rosemary, olive oil and paprika until all sides are coated well with spices. Roast approximately 40 minutes, turning occasionally, until tender. Let cool to room temperature. In large bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper. Add potatoes, onion and parsley. Toss to combine.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Prepare cooked pudding according to package directions. Remove from heat and add dry cake mix.
Mix well.
Spread batter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces and nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into serving size pieces.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cream of tartar and baking soda.
Pour over corn and stir until well coated.
Pour mixture in 2 cookie sheets and bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes. It should be crunchy.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage in small strips, starting with green leaves and place in waterless cookware.
Cook 5 minutes, then add rest of cabbage and cook about 10 to 12 minutes longer.
Turn off heat and browning pan until ready to serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, salt, margarine and cocoa.
Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add oats, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well; drop onto wax paper by spoonful and cool.
Don't refrigerate.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift
together dry ingredients.
Mix liquid ingredients together,
add
to	dry
ingredients and mix well.	Grease and flour pans. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 6 small loaves.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Put lemon Jell-O in 3/4 cup hot water.
Let cool while mixing other ingredients, then mix together and chill.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in hot oil until tender. Add remaining ingredients and stir to mix.
Bring to boiling and reduce heat.
Simmer with lid on for 20 minutes.

title: waldorf astoria red cake and frosting
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients well.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Sift together next 3 ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Mix together last 2 ingredients; stir in last.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: double delicious chicken
directions: Bring water to boil.
Stir in noodles and chicken cubes.
Boil for 7 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serves 6.

title: meara's dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Chop dried beef.
Chop green onions. Mix all ingredients together and serve with corn chips or crackers.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, soda and cinnamon in bowl.
Add eggs and fruit cocktail; mix with spoon. Bake for 45 minutes in greased and floured oblong pan.

title: spinach salad
directions: Brown the sesame seed
and almonds in the oven at 350°.
(Watch closely as they brown easily.)
Chop the lettuce and green onions together.
Shake the poppy seed, salad oil, sugar, pepper, salt and vinegar in a jar.
Toss with the greens.
Garnish with the sesame seed and almonds.

title: easy beef goulash
directions: Brown beef in skillet, stirring occasionally with a fork to break up the meat.
Drain off any excess fat.
Sprinkle uncooked noodles over meat; combine water, tomato sauce and onion soup mix. Pour over noodles in skillet.
Do not stir.
Reduce heat to moderately low and simmer 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southwest corn bread
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cumin; set aside.

title: yellow squash bake
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter in skillet. Stir in 4 ounces stuffing mix.
Add soup, sour cream, green onions, celery and carrot, stirring to mix.
Add drained squash. Place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining stuffing mix. Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown.
Freezes well.

title: gooey buns
directions: Finely chop bologna. Shred cheese.
Finely chop onion and pickle.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread mix on bun and top. Place in the oven at 325° for 25 minutes in foil or microwave in napkin for 30 seconds on High.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add a few shakes of Worcestershire sauce, onion salt, garlic powder and chili powder.
Combine ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sirloin tips
directions: Brown sirloin cubes in cooking oil.
Remove from skillet. Saute all other ingredients.
When done, add cooked sirloin cubes back in with other ingredients.
(Don't cook vegetables until soggy, let them be crisp.)

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake 2 layers of cake using mix.
Cut each in half, making 4 layers.
Combine sour cream, coconut and sugar.
Let mixture set until it blends nicely.
Put mixture between layers.
Cover cake with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: creole loaf cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat in the eggs. Sift together the flour, cocoa and salt; add alternately with the buttermilk to the sugar mixture.
Mix soda with the water; add to mixture last.
Bake in flat pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: glaze for strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook until clear.
Cool.
Drizzle over fresh berries in a prebaked pie shell.
Add red food coloring for color, if desired, to cooked mixture.

title: ranch pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Cool.
Mix noodles with all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in bowl in order given.
Mix well after each ingredient added.
Continue mixing until well blended.
Bake in 325° oven in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Stir beans and seasoning.
Heat thoroughly. Spread mixture in a 13
x 9-inch baking dish. Combine sour cream and picante dip.
Spread over beef mixture. Top with cheese and bake at 400° until bubbly (about 20 minutes). Serve with enchilada chips.

title: jalapeno cheese sandwichesroswell, new mexico
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This can be used on sandwiches as a dip or put on toast for a breakfast treat.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: Heat water and 1 teaspoon salt to boiling in 10-inch skillet. Add asparagus.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until stalks are crisp-tender, 8 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Arrange asparagus in square baking dish.
Shake oil, vinegar, oregano, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, mustard and garlic in tightly covered container.
Pour over hot asparagus, turning until well coated. Cover and refrigerate until chilled, 2 to 3 hours.

title: brownies(extra fattening, bigger butted women, beware!)
directions: Mix 1/2 can of milk, butter and cake mix.
If the batter is still dry, you may add a sprinkle of water.
Add the rest of the milk to the caramels and melt in the microwave or a double boiler. Pour 2/3 of the cake mixture into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan and bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from the oven and add a layer of nuts, caramel and chocolate chips.
Cover with the remaining cake mixture and bake an additional 20 minutes at 350°.

title: wassail punch
directions: Simmer the first 4 ingredients 10 minutes and strain. Add the orange juice, grapefruit juice and cider. Decorate with orange slices.

title: mushroom roast
directions: Shake flour in oven cooking bag.
Place roast in bag.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until done at 350°.

title: portuguese stuffing
directions: Saute onion and parsley in oil.
Add vinegar, paste, salt and pepper.
Simmer until blended.
In bowl, place bread and pour mixture.
Cool.
Add 2 eggs, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well. Return to hot pan and turn.
Cool until dry.
Make sure you can taste vinegar.
Stuff pork shoulder, turkey, etc.
Roast/bake as usual.

title: hello dollies
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Spread saltines on cookie sheet.
Melt butter.
Stir in sugar and microwave on High for 3 minutes or boil in saucepan on stove for 3 minutes.

title: turkey frame broth and soup
directions: Broth:
Break up carcass and place in large pot; add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil over high heat; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 2 hours.
Remove carcass and cool.
Remove turkey from bones and reserve (optional).
Discard carcass. Strain broth and discard vegetables and seasonings.

title: submarine salad
directions: Add pineapple, juice and all, into bowl.
Add pudding and beat 3 minutes.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Add nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place into 2 bread pans (loaves).
Bake at until done.
When cool, you can sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken flautas with salsa
directions: Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in broth, chicken and chilies.
Cook, stirring constantly, until very thick and bubbly.
Dip tortillas in 1/4-inch hot oil to soften.
Spoon a heaping tablespoon of filling in each tortilla and roll up.
Saute flautas, a few at a time, in hot oil, turning often until crisp, about 2 minutes.
Keep warm. Serve with Salsa.
Garnish with lettuce.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Roll and crush graham crackers fine.
Mix with sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: cathy's chicken hooters
directions: Mix the bread crumbs and Parmesan and spread them onto a dinner plate.
Melt the butter and brush it onto the chicken breasts.
Dip them into the bread crumbs/Parmesan cheese mixture.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Prepare Broccoli Spears according to package directions. Cooking only 5 minutes.
Drain and put into greased baking dish. sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350 for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
top with onion rings.
Bake 8-10 minutes longer until onions are crisp and golden brown.

title: layered lemon pie
directions: Use pastry cutter to blend.
Press into baking dish.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Let cool.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spray 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with Pam nonstick. Layer bottom of Pyrex dish with whole graham crackers.
Spread 1/2 of pudding mixture over the crackers.
Add another layer of whole graham crackers, then spread remaining pudding mixture.
Top with another layer of whole graham crackers.
Pour cooled icing over cake.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Top cake while hot.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: (This is an old German recipe that my Grandma Remmert made.)

title: no frost german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts and coconut on the bottom of the pan.
Mix cake mix per instructions on box and spread over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese and oleo.
Add powdered sugar and spoon over cake batter, leaving 1/2-inch from edge of pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.
Scoop out with spatula.

title: shrimp salad delight
directions: Chop shrimp into small pieces. Chop onion into fine pieces. Combine all ingredients together. Chill.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Let dough thaw until pliable.
Roll dough into a 10 x 14-inch rectangle.
Spread with melted butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over butter.
Cut into 10-inch long strip, 1/2-inch wide. Twist strips.
Bring the two ends together and twist.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet, 1 inch apart.
Do not let rise. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit balls
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in cold frypan.
Cook about 10 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir into it vanilla, 2 cups Rice Krispies and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Dip teaspoon in ice water, then drop by teaspoonfuls into flaked coconut.
Roll to coat evenly.
Chill before serving.
Makes about 35 (1 1/2-inch) balls.

title: buckeyes
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: breakfast before
directions: Saute sausage, drain on paper towel.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13-inch dish. Pour on egg mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot rolls(my mamma scritchfield's)
directions: Mix yeast cake with 1/2 cup of the warm water.
Mix all ingredients with half of flour.
Mix well and beat good by hand. Add rest of flour and mix well; let set until double in size. Reduce in size and place in refrigerator tightly covered.
Use as needed.

title: special k bars
directions: On stove, bring Karo and brown sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Slowly stir in Special K.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Pour chips on top; cover until chips melt.
Spread chips with knife.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Slice onion thinly and separate into rings. Combine vinegar, oil, Dr. Pepper, sugar, salt and pepper.
Shake vigorously.
Place drained vegetables and onion rings in a bowl. Pour the dressing over them and toss lightly.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Let stand approximately 24 hours, tossing together occasionally.
Serve on lettuce leaf or bed of salad greens. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Mix zucchini, green pepper, onion, salt and celery seed and let stand for 1 hour.
Then add sugar and vinegar.
Put into jars.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar, salt and flour in top of double boiler. Add milk, gradually, while stirring constantly.
Cook, over boiling water, until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Mix cornmeal, salt and pepper. Roll tomatoes in meal mixture.
Fry slowly until browned, turning once.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot. Serves 6.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the oleo, shortening and sugar for 5 to 7 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, just until mixed.
Fold in dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla until just mixed.
Bake in a 10-inch tube or large Bundt pan for 70 minutes at 325°; grease and flour pan or spray with Pam.

title: basic cream sauce
directions: In 1 1/2-quart microwave safe bowl, microwave butter and garlic on High 40 seconds or until butter is melted.
Using a wire whisk, stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Microwave on High 1 minute or until mixture foams.
Gradually add milk while stirring with a wire whisk.
Microwave on High about 4 minutes, stirring twice, until sauce is thickened.
Makes 1 cup.

title: jackie's dip
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor or blender and blend until smooth.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli and onion in butter on low heat.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup; stir until mixed.
Add rice.
Add mushrooms.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice and bean stuffed peppers
directions: In a large microwave casserole dish, combine corn, onion and water.
Microwave, covered, on High power for 2 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, uncooked rice, sugar and black pepper.
Microwave, covered, on High for 2 to 3 minutes, or until bubbly, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in beans, drained.
Cover.
Set aside.
Cut pepper in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Place pepper halves, cut side down, on microwave plate.
Cover with plastic wrap; open vent hole for steam.
Microwave on High for about 3 minutes or until nearly tender.
Drain.
Turn pepper halves, cut side up.
Mound rice mix into shells.
Microwave, covered, on High for 2 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn after first minute.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese after 2 minutes. Microwave another 30 seconds.

title: cinnamon cutouts(decorations)
directions: Be careful in your selection.
They are better if not too fresh.
Some choose them young, others want them old this is a matter of personal taste.
Do not boil.
Many insist upon keeping them in hot water, but this always makes them sour.
Be careful not to chill with indifference; instead keep them warm with the sunshine of smiles.
Even the poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good if spiced with the essence of love and a dash of play.
If treated this way, they will keep for years.

title: coffee cake
directions: Prepare cake mix
according
to
directions on the box. Mix together sour cream,
brown
sugar
and cinnamon.
Put 1/2 cake batter in a greased
pan.
Take
a
knife
and
swirl the brown sugar mixture through the other half of the batter, then pour on top of the other batter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chilled yellow tomato soup
directions: Combine half of the broth, yellow tomatoes, sweet pepper, banana peppers, garlic and onion in a food processor bowl container.
Cover and process or blend mixture until smooth. Repeat with the other half of the same ingredients.
Transfer soup to bowl.
Cover and chill for 4 hours.
To serve, pour soup into bowls or cups; sprinkle with chopped plum tomato and if desired, chives.

title: truffle cookies(yield: 6 dozen cookies)
directions: 1. Melt unsweetened chocolate, butter and 1 cup chocolate chips in a heavy 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Let cool.

title: dessert drink
directions: Coat rims of 4 tall stemmed glasses with lemon.
Dip in granulated sugar and set aside.
Place remaining ingredients except cream and cinnamon in 12-cup casserole.
Microwave 2 minutes, uncovered.
Pour into glasses and top with dollops of whipped cream.
Sprinkle with dash of cinnamon and serve immediately.

title: chicken pasta hot dish
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. In a large saucepan, melt butter. Stir in flour and salt. Blend in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Add cheese; stir until melted. Combine pasta, cheese sauce and chicken. Mix well. Pour into 3-quart casserole. Top with cornflake crumbs. Bake at 350° until hot, about 30 minutes.

title: orange beets
directions: In a sauce pan stir all of the above together cook until thick and then add the beets and heat till hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: heart smart baked chicken(main course)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place oatmeal, cheese, salt, pepper and paprika in blender; mix and place in shallow dish.
In a separate shallow dish, mix garlic and milk.
Place chicken 1 piece at a time in oatmeal mixture and then milk and then in oatmeal mix. Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle with oleo.
Bake 1 hour. For a healthy dish, remove skin from chicken.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together and pour into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour pineapple juice over cake while still warm.
Cool and remove from pan. Mix crushed pineapple, Cool Whip and pudding together. Spread on cooled cake.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: christmas wreath cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar with the next 5 ingredients on low speed of mixer until just mixed.
Increase speed to medium and beat 4 minutes, occasionally scraping sides of bowl with a spatula (mixture may look dry).
Preheat oven to 400°.
Take a heaping teaspoonful of dough at a time and roll into a 6-inch rope.

Place each dough rope on cookie sheet in a circle, crossing ends over. Brush cookies with egg white and sprinkle on some sugar. Decorate with red and green cherries. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until light golden brown. Allow wreaths to cool on cookie sheet. Store in a tightly covered container.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine
cocoa,
1 1/2 cups sugar and flour in a medium saucepan;
set
aside.
Beat
egg yolks.
Gradually stir yolks and milk
into
cocoa mixture;
add butter.
Cook over medium heat until
thick, stirring constantly.	Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour filling into baked pastry shell.

title: french bread*
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
While yeast softens, sift flour, salt and sugar together in large bowl.
Stir in the dissolved yeast.
Add just enough of the second cup of lukewarm water to make a soft, rather sticky dough.
Cover and place bowl in warm place to rise, at least double in size.
This will take 2 to 4 hours depending on the warmth of the kitchen.
When dough is high and spongy, punch it down and beat well with your hand. Divide bread into 2 parts and place each in a 6-inch greased round baking dish.
Cover and allow to rise until it reaches top of bowl.
Brush with melted butter to give flavor to crust and place in preheated oven (400°).
Bake for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, flour, salt and sugar.
Melt butter in baking dish. Add corn to butter; pour over egg mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: beefy tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Add soup and cheese; mix well.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Mix asparagus and mushroom soup together.
Add liquid from 1 can of asparagus.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in 2-quart casserole.
Chop hard-cooked eggs and place on mixture, making a layer of eggs. Pour remaining mixture in baking dish.
Then sprinkle top with cracker crumbs.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar.
Add milk and oil.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder; add to liquid mixture.
Stir only until blended.
Carefully fold in blueberries and nuts.
Pour into large, well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: 5 hour beef stew(servings:  8)
directions: In a good sized casserole or a small roaster, mix all ingredients (not necessary to brown meat).
Cover and bake in a 250° oven for 5 hours.
May be stirred once during cooking, but not really necessary.

title: "mustrola"(a family reunion tradition)
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add onion and butter to ground meat.
Stir in soups and pimento over medium heat.
Gradually add diced up cubes of Velveeta and stir until all melted.
Add macaroni shells.
Serve with salad!

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla and melted margarine together.
Add buttermilk and lemon juice.
Add well beaten eggs to mixture.
Add coconut and pecans last.
Stir well and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° about 40 minutes.
Serves about 24 slices.

title: mexican dish
directions: Mix in baking dish.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mock whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour in small pan over low flame until thick. Cool.
Blend butter and shortening with mixer.
Add sugar gradually and mix for another 4 minutes.
Add cooled milk paste. Mix for 2 to 4 minutes.
Fold in vanilla.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; roll into log shape on wax paper.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.
Slice thin and bake at 375°.

title: garlic swiss cheese spread
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, garlic and cheese.
Add more mayonnaise, if necessary, to make the mixture spreadable.
Place in a bowl, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Bring to boil peppers, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Boil 1 minute (a boil you cannot stir down).
Cool 10 minutes.
Add Certo and food coloring (enough to make a light green).
Wait 10 more minutes and skim off top to throw away.
Pour into jars.

title: round-'em-up burgers(makes 8 burgers)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Place the hamburger patties on two rimmed baking sheets. Spread the barbecue sauce evenly over the tops of the patties and sprinkle with the green chilies. Bake for 15 minutes. Top each burger with a slice of cheese and a sprinkle of French fried onions. Bake for 3 to 5 minutes or until no pink remains in the burgers and the cheese is melted. Serve in the buns.

title: stuffed mirlitons
directions: Boil mirlitons until tender.
Cut in half and scoop out centers.
Mash centers well, then place in pot with hot butter. Heat a bit, then add chopped ham, onion and shrimp.
Add salt and parsley.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add soaked bread and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Place in mirlitons shells or in casserole, sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake in 375° oven until brown and crisp.

title: economy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and place in refrigerator.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Yields enough for 50 cups.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Cream together eggs, oil and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients mixture gradually.
Blend in zucchini and nuts.
Pour batter into lightly greased and floured Bundt pan or can choose 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: transparent pie
directions: This makes 2 pies or 16 tarts.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear up toasted bread and place in 2-quart buttered casserole. Add cut apples.
Heat milk and butter until melted.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Stir in eggs.
Add raisins and pour onto bread mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Set dish in shallow pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes (until knife inserted is clean).

title: star-kist tuna special(by arthur godfrey)
directions: Melt butter, add flour and stir until smooth.
Blend in mushroom soup.
Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Add undrained peas and flaked tuna.
Season to taste.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: squash pickles
directions: Place vegetables in a large container. Sprinkle with salt and let stand for 1 hour. Drain, but do not wash. Bring vinegar, sugar and seeds to a boil. Boil 1 minute. Add vegetables. Bring to a hard boil and pack in jars.

title: play dough
directions: Stir together in pan flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Add oil and water.
Add food coloring.
Cook over medium heat until dough follows spoon.
Remove from heat.
Knead well until elastic.
Keep in plastic bag or covered bowl in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to come to room temperature.
Cut beef and onions into small pieces.
Save some of the beef to cover cheese ball.
Mix remaining beef, onions and cream cheese.
Add garlic powder to taste.
Form cheese mixture into a ball shape and cover with beef.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
In glass dish, dice chicken and spread evenly in the bottom.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter and pour over chicken.
Spread corn, peas, carrots and potatoes over chicken and butter.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Grease a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients for 1 minute on high speed in blender or for 2 minutes with hand beater. Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook and cool pasta.
Cook cubed chicken and 1/2 onion in large frying pan halfway through and add curry powder and 1/2 to 3/4 cup water.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Pour ice cubes over top of vegetables while preparing the syrup.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
With a meat mallet, flatten chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
Dip chicken into egg and then bread crumbs, coating thoroughly.
In medium skillet heat olive oil. Cook chicken in oil until well browned on both sides, pour spaghetti sauce into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on sauce and top with Parmesan cheese and shredded Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: salmon pate
directions: Mix all ingredients together until creamy.
Form in shape of a log and chill.
Serve on crackers.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Soak dried apples overnight.
In the morning, chop in small pieces and cook slowly in the syrup for 45 minutes.
While apples cool, pour sour cream into a bowl.
Add egg and beat thoroughly. Add sugar and continue to beat.
Sift flour; measure and add salt, soda and cloves.
Sift again.
Add sifted dry ingredients to mixture.
Beat thoroughly and then add apples.
Blend together. Pour into a 5 x 9 x 4-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes in small pieces. Chop onion. Cook onions and potatoes until tender in water. Add oleo, cream of chicken soup, salt and pepper to taste. (Need to thicken, add milk or water.)

title: company vegetables
directions: Cook each vegetable package separately for about 4 minutes only. Drain and combine in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with the cheese. Combine soup and milk and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with 1 can of onion rings.
Bake for another 8 to 10 minutes.

title: carrots plus
directions: Steam carrots.
In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter.
Add onions and cook over moderate heat.
Cover until they are transparent, about 10 minutes.
Add apple slices and cover.
Continue to cook, just until tender, but still hold their shape, about 5 minutes, depends on variety of apples used.
Drain carrots and add carrots to skillet; stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper; reheat.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in covered container.
To one cup of hot water, add mix to your taste.

title: orange-sherbet ice cream
directions: Add condensed milk and crushed pineapple into ice cream container.
Pour orange Crush to fill line.
Freeze until firm.

title: date squares
directions: Bring to boil until slightly thickened.
Cool.

title: old fashioned chocolate pudding
directions: Cook on low heat until thick.
Place vanilla wafers on bottom of dish and on side, then top pudding with meringue.

title: mashed carrots and parsnips
directions: Peel and slice carrots and
parsnips.
Bring
to a boil together in about 1 inch of water.	Reduce	heat to low, cover and simmer for about 20 minutes
or until tender.
Drain.
Add a little milk
and
the
butter,
return
to	heat and mash in saucepan with potato
masher.
Stir in brown sugar and salt to taste.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and crumble cheese crackers on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in chips and pecans.
Spread evenly over crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Cool. Cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: chocolate coconut balls
directions: Mix melted butter and nuts.
Add coconut, sugar, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into balls, size of a quarter.
Chill 15 minutes.
Melt wax and chocolate pieces in double boiler.
Use tongs.
Dip balls into mixture and place on wax paper to dry.

title: hamburger gravy(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Saute onion until clear; add meat and cook until brown.
Stir in mushrooms and gravy.
Simmer on low for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rub potatoes with the oil and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until soft when squeezed.
Allow to cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp, leaving the skin and about 1/2 of pulp intact.
Place the pulp in a large mixing bowl and set aside.

title: white sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Beat with a fork until there are no lumps.

title: tortellini alfredo
directions: In boiling water (salted, about palmful), cook tortellini according to package directions.
Drain.
Add butter and Parmesan. Toss until melted.
Add cream and vegetables.
Stir until warmed.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Sprinkle with crushed saltine crackers and the melted margarine.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cream drops
directions: Mix sugar, coconut, milk, pecans and butter until smooth. Shape into balls and chill overnight.
Prepare coating by melting chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Place toothpicks in cream drops and dip in coating once or twice.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients and let marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Blend all ingredients (except almonds) together until well mixed.
Spoon mixture into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers and raw veggies!

title: kolaches
directions: Heat milk, add shortening to dissolve, let cool to lukewarm. Add salt, egg yolks and egg, and sugar.
Add all of this to the yeast (which by this time should have risen to a foamy stage).
Add 3 cups flour first and beat with mixer until dough is smooth and shiny.
Then add the remainder of the flour, a little at a time, beating until smooth after each addition.
(After 4 to 5 cups of flour, you need to change to your dough hooks.)
The dough should be glossy; it will not be as thick as used for dinner rolls. Butter the dough and let rise in bowl until double in bulk, about one hour.
Cover the bowl of dough with a clean dish towel while it is rising.

title: zucchini-carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil together. Add sifted dry ingredients. Add zucchini, carrots, nuts and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes and remove from pan. Cool on rack.
Glaze, if desired.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat 1/2 cup of blue cheese with cream cheese on low speed, until well blended.
Add mayonnaise and half-and-half, beat on low speed until creamy.
Stir in reserved blue cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, onions, celery and green peppers well.
Mix sugar, oil and vinegar well and pour over kraut.

title: great-great grandmother's teacakes
directions: Put several cups of flour in bowl.
Make a nest in the flour. Start with butter and add all other ingredients.
Knead dough, using flour from nest.
Make dough as soft as possible for rolling.
Place on well floured board and roll approximately 1/4 inch thick.
Cut teacakes and place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 400° oven until light brown.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in large saucepan; heat to boiling.
Stir constantly about 5 minutes over medium heat; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir vigorously until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until tender 20 to 30 minutes. Combine sugar, salt, vinegar, flour, water, mustard and beaten egg. Cook over low heat until creamy and thick, stirring constantly. Add butter, whipping cream (not whipped) and mayonnaise.
Blend well and cool.
Remove skins from potatoes.
Slice potatoes and eggs into large bowl.
Cut onions into small pieces including tops. Add to potatoes.
Carefully fold in dressing.
Refrigerate at least 5 hours before serving.
Garnish as desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pet pecan pie
directions: Mix in bowl, flour, white sugar and salt.
Beat 2 eggs with fork, then add eggs, brown sugar, Pet milk, pecans and vanilla. Bake at 375° about 50 minutes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: numero uno
directions: In large skillet over medium heat warm oil, add the onions and cook, stirring occasionally until tender, about 20 minutes.
In a 4 1/2 to 5-quart heavy casserole or Dutch oven over medium heat, combine beef and pork.
Season with salt and cook, stirring often, until meat is brown, about 20 minutes.
Scrape the onions into casserole with the meat.
Stir in chili powder, cumin, oregano, cocoa, cinnamon and cayenne pepper and cook, stirring for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato juice and beef stock and bring to boil. Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Taste, correct the seasoning and simmer for 30 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in garlic.
To thicken the chili further or bind any surface fats, stir in the optional cornmeal.
Stir in beans and simmer another 5 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Heat juices in top of double boiler.
Beat 2 eggs.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to egg mixture; add this to juices.
Cook until thick. Put in refrigerator.
When cool, store in jar.
Pour over fresh fruit.

title: grandma yates' cookies
directions: Mix by hand; roll into small balls and mash with fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: oatmeal-spice cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves on a sheet of waxed paper.
Beat room temperature margarine and sugars in a large bowl, with electric mixer on high speed, until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture, then oats and nuts.

title: cream cheese-chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and set aside.
Slice first package of cookie dough 1/4-inch.
Line pan with slices.
Spread cream cheese over dough.
Slice second package of cookie dough on top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a 17 x 11-inch pan.

title: stovies(scottish stoved potatoes)
directions: Arrange potatoes and onions in layers in a large, heavy skillet.
Sprinkle each layer with salt, pepper and parsley.
Add oil.
Around edges of skillet, add a cup or so of stock or water. Cover tightly and simmer until potatoes are soft and most of the liquid has been absorbed, about 30 minutes.
If using an electric skillet, cook at about 325°.
Serves
6 to 8.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, over medium heat, melt chips and margarine with sweetened condensed milk, water and vanilla.
Cook and stir constantly until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix some more.
Whip the egg whites until they peak; fold egg whites into batter.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: baked pork steak
directions: Dip steak in egg, then in crumbs.
Brown in margarine.
Place in roaster.
Add water to half cover.
Season.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Add more water, if needed.

title: lentil soup
directions: While frying bacon, boil stock with lentils.
Turn down to simmer for 1/2 hour.
Saute onions in bacon grease.
Throw the bacon and onions in the pot.
Saute lightly, carrots and celery and seasonings.
Pour tomatoes over carrots and celery and simmer for 5 minutes.
Throw everything in the pot and simmer for another 1/2 hour.

title: zippy pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add to the other ingredients that have been assembled in a pan or bowl.
Mix thoroughly and pour into mold.
Cool in refrigerator.
Unmold. Reduce mayonnaise with cherry juice to serve as a dressing.

title: pecan peach cobbler
directions: In a bowl, combine the pie filling, water and nutmeg. Transfer to a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle with pecans. Separate the biscuits and arrange over the pecans. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown. Serve warm. Yield: 5 servings.

title: barb's famous potatoes
directions: Heat cream and butter together. Add salt. Place thawed potatoes in single layer pan. Pour cream mixture over the potatoes. Sprinkle cheese over potatoes. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: filling for punkin roll
directions: Fill and roll; wrap in foil.
Freezes well.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, onion, butter, salt and pepper in casserole dish.
Add milk.
Cover with foil and poke a few holes in it. Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.
Add cheese when done and melt, if desired.

title: sausage macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni to package directions.
Drain.
Fry sausage, onion and green pepper until lightly browned.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk, cook over low heat until thickened.
In greased casserole (1 1/2 quart) alternate layers of macaroni and cheese. Pour thickened sauce over layered macaroni and cheese.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry-apricot cooler
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill. Serves 9.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, then milk.
Add canned milk and cream. Pour in freezer and churn until done.
You can add about 2 pints crushed fruit, chocolate syrup or small jar peanut butter for variation.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil together, then add vinegar.
Add flour and soda gradually.
Then add buttermilk, vanilla and cake coloring.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into glass jar; cover.
Keep on hand in refrigerator.

title: punczki (raised donuts)
directions: Mix the yeast with 1/2 cup warm water.
Put the beaten eggs, lukewarm milk and yeast together, then beat the flour mixture a little at a time, then add the rest of the flour.
Let raise. When raised, take a little dough, pat out and cut with glass.
Let raise and deep fry three minutes on each side in Crisco.

title: old fashioned pie
directions: Mix well in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake for about 30 minutes at 250°.
Check for doneness, depending on individual ovens.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Fry cabbage, sugar and salt.
Cook until tender.
Cook noodles and drain.
Combine cabbage, noodles and bacon.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Spoon on sour cream; bake 5 more minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Combine all but chocolate chips. After all is melted, simmer 15 minutes. Test mixture to see if done by dropping a little in cold water to see if fudge holds its shape.
Add chocolate chips. Stir.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Enjoy!

title: red onion salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add taco mix and simmer according to package directions.
Add beans; heat through.
Transfer to chafing dish or small crock-pot.
Put the grated cheese on top. Pour the taco sauce over that.
Cover until cheese melts.
Dip chips into mixture.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend together the butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Form balls.
In a double boiler, melt the chips and wax.
Remove from heat, leaving over hot water.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: hot slaw
directions: Hand chop the first 5 ingredients. Mix the remaining ingredients together and bring to a boil. Pour over the cabbage. Seal and keep in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Into a large mixing bowl, measure flour, brown sugar, butter, white sugar, eggs, vanilla, soda and salt. Mix on low speed, scraping sides of bowl. Beat on medium speed until well blended. Stir in chips, candy and walnuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown. Cool slightly before moving to racks. Makes 3 dozen.

title: best layered salad
directions: Into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, tear washed lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Top with torn fresh spinach.
Crumble fried bacon on second layer.
Separate frozen peas and place on top of bacon. Chop green onions on top of peas (1 cup red onion rings may be substituted).
Sprinkle cheese evenly over previous layer.
Place chopped hard-cooked eggs over cheese.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and crumbled blue cheese and spread over top.
Chill overnight before serving.
Cut into squares for serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add corn syrup, butter and sugar and beat together. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in pie crust at 375° to 400° until done.
Makes 1 pie.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown meat and onion together and drain.
Mix corn with corn bread mix.
Add water; pour 1/2 corn bread mix in greased 12-inch iron frypan.
Layer meat and onion on top of corn bread mix, then the rest of corn bread mix.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican party dish
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Spread onto large platter or pizza pan.	Add salsa sauce over spread.
Top with shredded cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: christmas punch(served many times at school)
directions: Dissolve sugar in 2 cups hot water.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Combine all ingredients, except 7-Up, and freeze. Thaw to slush stage.
Pour 7-Up when ready to serve.
Serves 25 to 30 people.

title: raw cauliflower salad
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, salad dressing mix and parsley flakes.
Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and margarine; set aside.
Cream sugar and eggs. Alternate flour and soda with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons butter and flour.
Cook gently.
Remove from heat; stir in seasonings and cream.
Fold in beans.
Place in shallow 2-quart casserole.
Cover with cheese, then with crumbs, mixed with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Mix together the pineapple with juice, sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add white bread (crusts trimmed).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until lightly browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broccoli and water; heat on stove.
Add cheese and soup and stir in rice.
Bring to boil on top of stove.
Pour in 4-quart or oblong baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Place roast in crock-pot with fat side up.
Place stick of margarine on top of roast.
Shake 2 good dashes of cinnamon on top.
Cover and cook on slow for 8 to 10 hours.

title: chicken picatta
directions: Skin and wash chicken.
Pat dry.
Mix flour and spices together in pie plate.
Dredge chicken in flour and pound out with a meat mallet.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Cover bottom of Dutch oven with oil.
Brown garlic and onion. Add large can of strained puree.
Add all other.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add cooked macaroni and sausages.

title: skyline chili spaghetti(famous cincinnati chili)
directions: Cook the noodles per the directions on the bag; drain.
Put back in the pan over low heat.
Immediately stir in the 2 cans of soup.
When finished, stir in tuna.
Heat to desired temperature. Season to taste and serve.
Serves 4 people.
Cooking time:
12 to 15 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar, salt and oil.
Add 2 cups flour and beat smooth.
Add 1 cup flour and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; cover.
Let rise until double.
Punch down.
Divide in half and spread in 2 greased pans.

title: ham on a grill
directions: Put the ingredients in blender and mix.
Marinade ham slices overnight.
Baste and turn frequently on an open grill.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: louie's pasta with clam sauce
directions: Wash anchovies in cold water.
Heat oil and butter.
Add garlic and onion.
Cook until brown.
Add anchovies.
Add parsley, rosemary, clam juice, and wine.
Bring to a boil.
Salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add clams.
Serve over linguine.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients in heavy skillet for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies. Fold in vanilla.
Let cool.
Roll into balls, then in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on crackers.

title: cherry delight pie
directions: Mix together and pour in graham cracker pie shells.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Place pecans in food processor. Process using on/off pulsing action until pecans are ground, but not pasty. Beat butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar in large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed until light and fluffy, scraping down side of bowl once. Gradually add 1 cup flour, vanilla and salt. Beat at low speed until well blended, scraping down side of bowl once.
Stir in remaining flour and ground nuts with spoon.

title: busy day turkey loaf
directions: Combine stuffing mix, croutons and milk in large mixing bowl. Let stand 5 minutes or until croutons are softened.
Add egg whites, Worcestershire sauce, onions and salt.
Beat well.
Add ground turkey.
Mix until combined.
Shape into loaf.
Place in foil-lined shallow baking pan.
Score loaf by making diagonal grooves across top.
Stir together ketchup, mustard and sugar. Spread over top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until browned.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs, then bananas, sour cream and lemon juice.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add to mixture, stirring just to dampen flour. Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove and finish cooling on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat in saucepan; bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well and drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: starter for sourdough bread
directions: Let stand 24 hours.
Make bread by the usual recipe for Sourdough Bread.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and peanut butter.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of floured fork to make crisscross.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook 1/2 package egg noodles.
Drain and put in bottom of deep baking dish.
Cook crumbled hamburger until brown.
Add onion, green pepper, 1/2 cup celery, mushrooms and tomatoes (chopped). Use 1/2 package of Sloppy Joes mix and 1 small can tomato sauce. Dash 3 or 4 teaspoons tomato catsup in; salt and pepper.
Cook until thick and pour over noodles.
Put some strips of cheese over this and put in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sweet potato surprise balls
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except marshmallows and oil; mix well.
Chill for easier handling.
Mold sweet potatoes around marshmallows; shape each into a ball and roll in additional crushed corn flakes.
Refrigerate to set.
Fry in deep oil at 375° for about 3 to 4 minutes or until lightly browned; drain well.

title: italian coconut cake
directions: Cream with 8 ounces of cream cheese.
Put coconut on top & between layers.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and beaten egg; mix well.
Drop mixture by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Press down the tines of fork.
Sprinkle sugar on top and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in pie pan.
Pour cinnamon and water mixture over apples.
Prepare streusel topping by mixing together butter, sugar and flour with a fork.
Sprinkle mixture over apples and bake in a 350° oven until crispy and golden brown.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: cherry "dump" cake
directions: "Dump" the pie filling in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
"Dump" the pineapple on as the next layer.
"Dump" the cake mix.
Evenly sprinkle the melted margarine.
"Dump" the coconut!
"Dump" the pecans!
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Good when warm.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and let stand in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix and serve over lettuce. Refrigerate.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Soften cookie dough (1 hour).
Spread on pizza pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.
Blend the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip; spread over cooled "cookie."
Top with fruit.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease and flour 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1 1/8-inch pan.
Whip eggs until thick and foamy (about 5 minutes).
Add sugar gradually to eggs.
Fold in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift together dry ingredients and fold into egg mix beating until smooth.
Pour into pan and spread to corners.
Sprinkle with nuts and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375° or until cake springs back to touch.
Immediately loosen and invert on a towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar. While hot, roll cake and towel from narrow end.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: quick crescent puff
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat a baking sheet with nonstick spray.
Unroll one can of dough; place on baking sheet.
Pinch and press perforations and seams to seal.
In a small bowl, stir preserves and 1/4 cup of the nuts until blended.
Spread on dough on baking sheet to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Separate triangles from second can of dough and arrange on top, leaving slits between triangles and overlapping as needed.
Pinch along edges of rectangle to seal.
Bake for 14 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack for 5 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Arrange in layers.
Put bacon bits on when ready to serve. Let salad set for 4 hours before serving.

title: maurice salad
directions: Cut up lettuce.
Add to lettuce the chicken, ham and cheese; mix well.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; peel them, slice thin and set aside.
Fry bacon; crumble and add to potatoes.
Saute onion in bacon drippings; then add dry ingredients and cook until bubbly.
Add water and vinegar and cook for about 2 minutes.
Mix with potatoes and serve.
This can be made ahead and heated in the microwave.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix eggs and sugar with fork.
Bring milk to a boil and mix with egg and sugar mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Place stick of margarine on top and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pecan chews
directions: Place softened margarine in bowl. Add white sugar and 2 cups flour. Mix thoroughly with hands and pat firmly into ungreased 11 x 16 jelly roll pan. Bake in 350° oven 12 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in medium bowl.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
Chill overnight for best flavor.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Microwave ground beef for 2 to 3 minutes; mix with spaghetti sauce and water and set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and pepper in a bowl.
Spoon 1/2 cup of meat sauce and spread on bottom of glass dish, then put a layer of uncooked noodles and 1/2 of the cottage cheese mixture.
Next, add a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat again, forming 2 layers.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 8 minutes, then on 50% power for 30 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese and let stand covered for 15 minutes before serving.

title: crunchy crab salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice on crabmeat.
Add peas, celery, onion and mayonnaise to crab mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve over chow mein noodles, if desired.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix well.
Grease and flour pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: chow mein
directions: Boil for 1 minute.
Put in lightly greased casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with chow mein noodles.

title: campfire pocket stew
directions: Prepare a good bed of coals.
For each person to be served, wash and slice thinly a potato, carrot, onion, 1/4 green pepper and a small handful of fresh green beans.
Add several chunks of cheese and salt and pepper.
Wrap in 2 large cabbage leaves.
Wrap all in aluminum foil, shiny side in.
