Cook on the coals for 15 minutes on each side.

title: chinese "cha shiv" marinade
directions: In a
small mixing bowl, combine garlic, pepper, ginger, soy sauce,
honey,
sherry,
Five-Spice powder and chili sauce. Mix well.
Trim all
but
1/2-inch
of fat from edges of chops. Place chops in marinade mixture.
Let stand for approximately 1 to 2 hours.
Place
chops in baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours, depending upon doneness, baste every 1/2 hour if desired.

title: hot spice percolator punch
directions: Put juices and water in a 30 cup percolator.
Put sugar and spices in basket of percolator.
Perk for 10 minutes.
Makes 30 cups.

title: van's grilled herb marinated chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in mixture for 1 to 24 hours.
Grill and brush chicken with marinade.
Grill until chicken is cooked.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Soften oleo to room temperature.
Mix oleo, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Blend in flour.
Add vanilla.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
May chill overnight.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar (2 tablespoons).
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: skewered chicken
directions: Skin and debone breasts; cut into strips 1 1/4-inch wide and 1/4-inch thick.
Place on metal skewers in a 9 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch dish.
Mix rest of ingredients well and pour over chicken.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Drain and grill over coals 3 to 4 minutes per side.

title: apple mystery delight
directions: Lightly grease and 8x12 baking dish.
Pour pineapple into dish.
In a bowl mix apples, 1/4 cup of sugar and lemon juice. Lay on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle with cake mix.
Top with melted butter, remaining sugar and pecans.
Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Take out and cut into squares, bake an additional 30 minutes.
May be served warm topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: 4 cheese pasta
directions: Fluff Ricotta with fork; thin to creamy consistency with cream or milk.
Mix in Fontinella and Mozzarella.
Let stand while cooking pasta.
Drain liquid from tomatoes.
Place cooked pasta in heated bowl and toss with oil.
Add cheese mixture and toss until it begins to melt.
Spoon tomato mixture over top; toss at table and pass the Romano.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Melt shortening in large skillet.
Coat chicken with flour.
Cook in shortening over medium heat until light brown.
Remove chicken; set aside.
Add onions, green peppers and garlic to pan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until onions and peppers are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Add chicken to sauce; cover tightly and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice or spaghetti.

title: glorified rice
directions: Cook rice in salted water (fluffy).
Add all fruit, nuts, sugar and whipped cream.
Add vanilla.
Fold into rice mixture.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Prepare and cook potatoes.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix remaining ingredients in 8-inch skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Add sweet potato slices.
Stir gently until glazed and heated through.

title: 24 hour salad no. 1
directions: In
large
deep salad bowl put layer of lettuce (broken in pieces).
Add layer of spinach, layer of cauliflower, layer of onion,
layer
of bacon, layer of mushrooms, layer of eggs and layer of peas over the top.
Do not toss.

title: cotton picking good cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and oil.
Beat well.
Add oranges; beat until oranges are torn up.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in layers at 350° until done.
Mix Cool Whip, instant pudding and pineapple; spread on layers.
Keep cool.

title: great salsa
directions: Drain tomatoes, saving juice for another use.
In mixing bowl, combine tomatoes, chilies, green onions, lemon peel, salt, oregano, pepper and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant
into
bite
size	pieces.
This will take approximately four	weeks.	Next
brown
at about 450° using a kerosene stove.
Don't
forget
to	salt
and pepper to taste. Use only enough
water	to
make
a good gravy and to keep the elephant from
burning to a crisp.	This could take six weeks. It will
feed	about
people if they aren't too hungry. Should more be expected, add the 2 rabbits, only if absolutely necessary because few people like Hare in their stew.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Put drained pineapple in casserole dish. Mix sugar, flour and pineapple juice in microwave dish. Cook in microwave until thin and sugar is dissolved. Pour over pineapple. Put cheese over pineapple. Put crushed crackers over cheese. Pour melted margarine over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over shredded wheat and raisins or dates. Stir together the eggs, salt, salad oil and sugar.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and cereal.
Put all together in a large container in refrigerator; it will keep up to 6 weeks.
To bake, just remove the amount you want and refrigerate the rest.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients per instructions on pudding box. Use half and half in place of milk. Cook peanut butter, chocolate chips and 4 tablespoons half and half until melted together. Place in bottom of graham cracker crust (1st layer). Take 1/2 of hot vanilla pudding and add 4 ounces of chocolate chips and blend and pour into pie shell (2nd layer). Take other 1/2 of pudding and add 4 ounces of peanut butter chips and blend and pour into pie shell (3rd layer). Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: swiss steak mozzarella
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces; coat with flour.
Melt butter in skillet.
Brown meat on both sides.
Add tomatoes, salt, basil and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook 25 to 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Cover meat with cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese melts.

title: aunt lois' baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, milk, cornstarch, salt (to taste).
Add corn.
Pour into glass pie pan or casserole dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Add margarine and stir. Bake additional 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top is light golden brown.

title: potato chip shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add 1/2 flour and mix well. Then mix remaining flour to butter and sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Take wooden spoon and stir in potato chips well. Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.

title: spanish steak
directions: Brown steak in vegetable oil; simmer in a little water until it starts to get tender.
Add tomatoes, onion, chili powder, garlic, oregano and bay leaves.
Cook until it is done; add mushrooms.
This can be eaten on cooked rice or wide noodles.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Split chiles and remove seeds.
Use deep, large casserole dish.
Line bottom of dish with half of chiles. Cover with half of Cheddar.
Repeat layer.
Mix eggs and flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chiles and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cover with Jack cheese and tomato sauce.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Watch so cheese does not burn.

title: applesauce chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients with spoon "well."
Put 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet pan.
Bake 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: new year punch
directions: Simmer sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Chill fruit juices and 7-Up.
At serving time, combine sugar syrup and fruit juices in punch bowl.
Slowly add 7-Up.
Add 7-Up ice cubes. Garnish with lemon or orange slices, if desired.
Makes about 25 (4-ounce) servings.

title: nut filled muffins
directions: Mix together and make little 1-inch balls.
Butter pans; place into pans and spread out 72 balls (1-inch).
Need small muffin pans 2-inches in diameter.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Chop onion.
Brown hamburg and onion in large pot.
Drain off fat.
Add water and bouillon cube.
Wash and chop potato and carrots.
Wash and shred cabbage.
Add potato, carrots and cabbage.
Bring to a boil.
Sprinkle rice into the mixture.
Add pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add tomatoes.
Heat to simmering and serve.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Stir in beans, barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Separate biscuits and then cut in half crosswise.
Place biscuits, cut side down, over hot meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: punch
directions: Prepare
Kool-Aid
as directed on packages.
Add orange juice and serve over ice.

title: "cajun" chili
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook all ingredients up to 2 hours, then add rest of ingredients.
(Add 1 to 2 cups water if thick.)
Simmer for hours!
Season to taste.
(Chili powder, cajun sunshine, garlic, etc.)

title: won ton cups
directions: Place won ton skins in tassie or muffin pan (take all 4 corners to center and place in pan; fold open).
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.

title: egg roll muffins
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; add sugar.
Mix flour and salt and add 1/2 this mixture to yeast mixture.
Mix well with wooden spoon until smooth.
Add egg and softened butter; mix well.
Add remaining flour.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled. Stir down and spoon into 12 well-greased muffin cups.
Let rise. Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: farmer's vegetable soup
directions: In pot, saute onion and leeks until limp.
Add stock, potatoes and tarragon.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Puree or mash with potato masher.

title: classic hollandaise(good for asparagus, broccoli, cauliflower, or eggs benedict.)
directions: In top of double boiler place egg yolks and 1/3 of butter. Over hot, not boiling, water, stir rapidly with a wooden spoon until butter melts.
Add second piece of butter,
continue stirring as mixture thickens and butter melts.
Add third piece of butter, stirring constantly.
(Water in bottom of double boiler should not come to a boil.)
When all butter is melted remove pan from hot water, stir rapidly 2 minutes longer.
Stir in lemon juice a tsp. at a time.
Add seasonings.
Place sauce again over hot water, stir constantly until thickened (2-3 minutes).
Remove from heat at once.
If sauce should curdle, stir in 1-2 Tbsp. of boiling water.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: karo classic pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together eggs, Karo, sugar, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: texas tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Add vanilla. Stir in sifted flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Roll between sheets of waxed paper sprayed with nonstick cooking spray and floured.
Cut out with cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: patriotic gelatin salad
directions: In separate bowls, dissolve each package of jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour one bowl of blue jello in fluted tube pan.
Chill until almost set, about 30 minutes.
Set other 3 bowls aside at room temperature.
Soften unflavored gelatin in remaining cold water.
Let stand 5 minutes. Heat milk in a saucepan over medium heat just below boiling.
Stir in softened gelatin and sugar until dissolved.
Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream and vanilla until smooth.
When blue jello in pan is set, carefully spoon 1 1/2 cups sour cream mixture over it. Chill until almost set, about 30 minutes.

title: spicy chicken gumbo
directions: Saute first four ingredients in large heavy kettle.
Blend in flour.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer one hour.
Add 2 - 3 cups cooked chicken, diced.
Simmer briefly.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup Colby cheese; mix well.
Turn into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Top with remaining cheese; bake 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: see's fudge(fantastic fudge)
directions: Cook together the sugar, butter and Pet milk for 18 to 20 minutes or until soft ball in cold water.
Stir often while cooking.
Watch, so it does not boil over.

title: lottie's hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add ingredients and milk alternately, beating lightly.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 10-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.
The crust will form on the bottom.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well. Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and add to the first mixture.
Add and stir by hand the apples and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Melt butter in large pan and stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Stir powdered sugar until thoroughly mixed.
Press in an 8-inch square pan.
Cover with melted chocolate.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: corn flake drops
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: vegetable ham soup
directions: Rinse and soak beans overnight.
Combine beans, bone and water in large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Remove ham and bone.
Chop ham and add ham and remaining ingredients to beans.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: k.c.'s infamous slime
directions: Mix cold water and glue in separate bowls.
Mix hot water, Borax and food coloring.
Add mixtures together and stir until well mixed.
Knead.
Store in a baggie.

title: pink punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Dissolve drink mix in cold water; add sugar and stir well. Add pineapple juice and gelatin. Refrigerate. Add 7-Up and sherbet just before serving. Yield: 35 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Mix well. Roll out on floured board and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute red and green peppers briefly in a small amount of butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix liquids, butter, potatoes, onions and cook until done.
Mix cracker crumbs, flour and seasonings.
Add to potato and onion mixture.
Add red and green peppers, mix well.
Bring to a boil, add cream
and corn, simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hoppin john
directions: Wash black-eyes in 5 cups boiling water. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and soak overnight.

title: great fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream and strawberry sauce together.
Mix all fruit together and add sour cream and sauce to salad.
I sometimes add a package of frozen fruit.
Make a few hours ahead.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Do not grease or flour pan.

title: phil's easy baked chicken
directions: Prepare rice according to directions on package.
Combine prepared rice, cream of chicken soup, Worcestershire sauce and poultry seasoning in a 2-inch baking pan.
Smother chicken breasts in rice combination.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch baking dish.
Combine flour and sugar. Add milk.
Pour into the middle of the melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit into middle of dish and do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour depending on the depth of the dish. Serves 6.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together in large bowl and set aside. Combine remaining ingredients together in bowl and then pour over dry ingredients and mix just until moistened.
Spray 12 muffin cups with Pam and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick beer bread
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Stir in the beer.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake 45 minutes at 350° or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: paul's slaw
directions: In small saucepan, combine mayonnaise, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Stir frequently, cooking over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool.

title: seven cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Refrigerate for several hours. Serves 12.

title: crispy catfish
directions: Clean and wash fish; have damp.
Place meal in a bag.
Add the seasonings to suit your taste.
Shake bag to mix seasonings and corn meal.
Add fillets to bag, a few at a time.
Shake bag to coat well.
Shake off excess meal.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: squash
directions: Cut up squash in slices with onions.
Let boil in water 20 minutes or until soft.
Drain and mash liquid out of squash.
In a casserole dish, break up bread into little pieces.
Add butter, egg, salt and pepper.
Add squash, cover and cook for 15 minutes or until heated well in 350° oven.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and freeze.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer 2 hours before.
Add one 2 liter bottle of ginger ale.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat well with mixer first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and fold together real well.
Make the day before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: no eggs chocolate cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients into an oblong cake pan; level down. Make 3 holes in the dry mixture.
Add 1 of the ingredients (Wesson oil, vinegar or vanilla) to each hole.
Over all this, pour 2 cups cold water, then mix all together in pan with spoon.
Level down. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: *One cup milk and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and melted shortening to eggs. Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: baked ham slices
directions: Spread ham slices with prepared mustard and peanut butter. Put one slice on top of the other.
Pour two cups of juice over ham.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°.
Add wine.
Bake another hour.
Place apricot (or cherries) on top and pour 1/2 cup honey.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Serves 10.

title: broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Melt cheese in cream of chicken soup.
Cook broccoli and cauliflower; mix with cheese and soup.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.

title: pocket lunch
directions: Use your favorite bread dough mix.
Mix accordingly.
Let rise.
Pat down.
Divide into pieces and roll out.
Place filling of choice on end of rolled dough.
Pull end over end and pinch edges together.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Great with mustard!

title: cookie brittle recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients by hand for best results.
Blend sugar, butter and vanilla until smooth.
Gradually add flour.
Then add nuts and chips to mix, stirring until all ingredients are well combined.
Then press the mixture onto a cookie sheet (17 x 11 x 1-inch).
Bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Watch closely (burns easily). Partially cool in pan; then break out of pan into irregular pieces.
Place onto paper towels or brown paper bags to finish cooling.

title: magic lemon meringue pie
directions: Back when Grandmother (Myrtle Olivia Harper Morace) was a girl, there were box lunches - a sort of picnic where the eligible young ladies made a dinner for two.
These box lunches were auctioned off to the eligible young men of the community.
Then the couple would have the box lunch "picnic style" at the gathering.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Combine vanilla pudding mix and milk in a mixer bowl; beat well.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries until separated and partially thawed.
Break cake into bite-sized pieces.
Alternate layers of cake, pudding, gelatin mixture and whipped topping, 1/2 at a time, in a large trifle bowl.
Refrigerate until serving time.
You can garnish with fresh strawberries, if in season.

title: tea strawberry slush
directions: Steep tea using 2 cups of water and chill.
In a blender, combine tea, strawberries and lemonade concentrate.
Process until smooth.
With blender running, gradually add about 1 cup ice cubes, processing until ice is melted.
Garnish with fresh fruit.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: trash
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Melt butter and add seasonings to butter. Pour over dry ingredients and mix thoroughly. Divide mixture over 2 cookie sheets. Cook at 325° for 1 hour, turning every 20 minutes during that hour. Cool thoroughly before placing in containers so that it will not be soggy. Enjoy.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Bring to boil the sugar and karo, remove from heat and stir in the peanut butter and cereal.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt the chips and spread over top.
Chill.

title: overnight breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer in it the bread, cheese and ham.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over the bread mixture.
Melt 1 cube margarine and pour over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: granny's cranberry sauce
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in sugar; set aside.
Grind cranberries and orange in a blender or food processor.
Add ground cranberries and orange to the jello mixture.
Stir in the pineapple and juice, pecans and celery.
Refrigerate to set.

title: copper carrots
directions: Mix well vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, oil, mustard and soup.
Mix vegetables and store in refrigerator.

title: fried chicken(yummy)
directions: Use thin boneless pork chops. Dredge pork chops in milk. Then shake them in a bag of Progresso Italian bread crumbs (flavored) with 1/2 tablespoon of Italian seasoning, dash of garlic salt and paprika (1/2 teaspoon) added to bread crumbs. Take frying pan with olive oil in nonstick pan and saute breaded chops on both sides until brown. Put into a baking dish with a lid. First layer is celery stalks, about 6 to 7-inches long, then put the browned pork chops in, then cover with celery and keep on layering and finish with celery. Cover. Add between 1/4 to 1/2 cup water. Cook at 375° for first 45 minutes, then at 340° for 30 minutes.

title: cappuccino pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to pkg directions using milk and coffee granules.
Fold into 1/2 cup prepared cool whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours.
To serve, garnish with remaining cool whip.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Combine flour, salt and vanilla and add to creamed mixture. Chill dough for 4 hours before rolling on a floured board.
Cut out cookies in desired shapes from dough and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Decorate as desired.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Sift flour and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased bundt pan.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve warm or cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil and mix well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Gradually add dry ingredients to egg mixture. Mix well and add balance of ingredients.
Batter will be very stiff, resembling a fruit cake batter.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Spread with glaze while warm.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and immediately add frozen orange concentrate.
Add mandarin slices and pineapple.
Chill until well set.

title: italian pot roast
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown roast in oil on all sides over medium-high heat; drain.
Combine the broth, tomato paste, mushrooms, onion, garlic, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper; pour over roast.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 3 to 3 1/4 hours or until the meat is tender.
Remove roast; keep warm.
Pour pan drippings and loosened browned bits into a measuring cup.
Pour drippings into a saucepan.
Combine flour and water until smooth; gradually stir into drippings.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Slice roast; serve with gravy.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: gridiron gumbo
directions: Drain and coarsely chop tomatoes, reserving juice.
Combine tomatoes, juice, chicken, ham, onion, celery, garlic and thyme in large skillet.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: cock of the walk cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add more sugar if cabbage is bitter. Let stand 12 to 24 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except milk, in heavy saucepan.
Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Add milk; cook 5 minutes longer. Serve hot.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix fruit with 1 cup of flour; set aside.
Mix butter, brown sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon and soda.
Blend in milk. Mix all together and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Place close together and bake 20 minutes in a 300° oven.
Makes a lot of cookies.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in an airtight container.
Great for camping trips!

title: martha's potato souproswell, new mexico
directions: Take 1/2 pkg. of frozen hash browns and cover with water and cook until done.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute green pepper in butter over low heat.
Blend in soup and milk; stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat slowly. Stir to prevent scorching.
Serve on fluffy boiled rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape mixture into loaf in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix vegetables with oil.
Bring sugar, vinegar and water to a boil.
Pour over vegetables; mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: coffee parfait
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in coffee.
Add salt.
When cold, add whipped cream.
Pour into sherbet glasses and chill.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix pudding mix, ice cream and milk; pour over crust. Refrigerate and firm up. Add Cool Whip and chocolate chips.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain off grease.
Add all ingredients, except tortillas and cheese.
Mix well.
Grate cheese and spray casserole with Pam.
Tear up tortillas in pieces and line casserole.
Put layer of meat mixture and layer of cheese.
Continue layers until all is used making sure cheese is last layer.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour in ring mold.

title: brownie pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and baking powder. Stir in remaining ingredients, except cream.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar to cream.
Whip until stiff.
Cover pie with whipped cream. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: jello and angel food salad
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with cake broken in small pieces.
Dissolve jello in water.
Stir thawed strawberries in jello.
Pour over cake.
Refrigerate.
Top with whip cream before serving.

title: mushroom burgers
directions: Pat out ground beef into patties.
Brown, then drain off the fat.
Mix mushroom soup and water together.
Pour over patties. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes or with rice.

title: cheesy tuna 'n rice muffinlettes
directions: Combine rice, cheese, tuna, olives, onion, parsley and seasoning salt.
Stir in eggs and milk, mixing thoroughly.
Spray six muffin cups with Pam.
Divide rice mixture evenly among cups. Bake 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Scrape and cut carrots; boil until tender.
Add teaspoon sugar to water.
Drain and cool in salad bowl.
Alternate carrots, peppers and onions.
Pour mixture, then add next layer.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Cover and let stand at least 24 hours. (Keeps up to 3 weeks.)

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with bread slices. Top with sausage, cheeses, then mushrooms.
Combine mustard with milk.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: party mints
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into little balls. Press down with a fork.
Makes approximately 100 mints.

title: lemon couscous chicken
directions: In a large skillet, bring water, oil, broccoli and contents of the spice sack from the couscous mix to a boil. Stir in the couscous, chicken, lemon juice and lemon peel. Remove from the heat. Cover and let stand for 5 minutes. Fluff lightly with a fork. Chill well and serve cold.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in oil until tender.
Add salt, cheese and soup; stir until cheese is melted and soup is well blended and bubbly.
Place in buttered casserole.
Bake, covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with crumbs; continue baking until browned, about 15 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Halve peppers lengthwise; discard stems and seeds.
Parboil peppers in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain and place in shallow baking dish with 1/8-inch of water.
Brown sausage well in a skillet; drain well, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Add contents of vegetable/seasoning packet and water to sausage and reserved drippings in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 6 minutes.
Add stuffing crumbs and corn; stir just to moisten.
Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon into pepper halves.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Cook bacon in a 9-inch cast-iron frying pan until crisp. Remove bacon; crumble and set aside.
Drain and save drippings. Put 1 teaspoon back in pan and set in oven at 400° while mixing other ingredients.
Beat eggs in large mixing bowl; stir in milk, 3 tablespoons drippings, meal and all other ingredients, including bacon chips.
Remove the pan from oven; pour batter in pan and put a tablespoon of the bacon drippings over top.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until brown.
If you don't want this hot, omit 1 pepper.

title: tofu-tuna bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine tuna, mayonnaise, onions, pimentos, lemon juice, cheese and peas in a medium-size bowl.
Mix well, then stir in tofu.
Spoon mixture into baking dish, sprinkle with almonds and wheat germ, and bake for about 45 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Serve immediately, or chill and slice for sandwiches.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: aunt betty's dill pickles
directions: In bottom of each quart jar, put 1 grape leaf, 2 garlic cloves and 1 tablespoon dill seed.
Slice cucumbers and put in jars. Cook salt, vinegar and water in a pot until boiling.
Pour liquid over pickles.
Seal and process 8 to 10 minutes, or until they change color.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: grandma's baked beans
directions: Saute onions and peppers with cooked bacon.
Throw off excess grease.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with salt.
Let stand for 1 hour and drain well.
Combine sugar, vinegar and celery seed and bring to a boil. Let this syrup mixture cool, then pour over cucumbers.
Add 1 onion.
Pack into pint jars and store in refrigerator.
Pickles will be ready to enjoy in about 3 days.

title: dessert
directions: Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan in a 300° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: nut crescents
directions: Thoroughly mix shortening, 3/4 c. sugar, egg milk and vanilla. Mix in sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread 1/4 of dough very thinly and evenly on greased inverted 9 X 9 X 2 pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/2 c. sugar and nuts.
Repeat.
Bake one pan at a time at 325 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.
While layer is hot, cut into 4 1/4 X 3/4 inch strips and shape over rolling pin.
Repeat until all dough is used.
If strips become to brittle to shape, soften in oven.
Yield 9 dozen.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix together.
Dip your food into and deep fry.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish in oven.
Shake potatoes in half flour and half Parmesan cheese mixture.
Place potatoes in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.
Turn after first 30 minutes.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and creme de menthe.
Spread on cooled brownies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter; cook and drain broccoli according to directions on package.
Heat soups and Cheez Whiz until thoroughly mixed.
Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: berry crunch
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with fruit; pour sugar over.
Next put dry jello following with dry cake mix, then water; on top, arrange the 4 pats of butter or margarine.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Bake in three 8-inch cake pans or 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, excluding ginger ale.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves about 25.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice.
Add apples; cover and simmer until tender. Blend cornstarch with enough water to make a smooth paste.
Stir in cornstarch; add spice and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter and add a second crust.
Bake at 350°.
(Add Sweet 'N Low if you choose, as apples vary in sweetness.)

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cream shortening and margarine.
Then add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Then add flour alternately with 7-Up and extracts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onion and celery in margarine. Add rice to broccoli and remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's white bread
directions: Scald milk.
Pour into bowl, add sugar, salt, shortening and hot water.
Stir until shortening is melted.
Cool to lukewarm, add yeast which has been crumbled into 1/4 cup lukewarm water and stirred until softened.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat applesauce.
Dissolve gelatin in hot applesauce.
Add 7-Up or Sprite and chill.
Mix in large pan as the soda will make foam.

title: czechoslovakian babovka(sponge cake)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in tablespoon of sugar and set aside to rise for 15 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup flour and let rise until spongy and light, about 30 minutes.

title: martha's sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in water until soft.
Peel potatoes; place in bowl.
Add butter and mash until smooth.
Combine sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven; place marshmallows on top.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: braised sauerkraut
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Saute onion until golden brown.
Stir in sauerkraut and apple slices.
Pour in bouillon and place bacon slices on top.
Cover; simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Add grated potato and continue to simmer until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove bacon and serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate covered strawberries
directions: Heat chocolate chips and squares with oil over low heat in double boiler.
Dip cleaned and dried berries into chocolate. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Yields about 35 pieces.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Mix all items together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: stroganoff
directions: In a skillet, cook beef and onion until no longer pink.
Stir in mushrooms, flour, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes.
Add chili sauce and worcestershire sauce, reduce heat, cook uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream just before serving and heat through (do not boil).
Serve over hot noodles.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Simmer mincemeat, raisins and water for five minutes.
Mix together the dry ingredients, add to mincemeat mixture, then the vanilla and eggs.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: bar-b-q chicken
directions: Mix and pour over chicken (chicken can be cut up or whole). Bake at 350 degrees until chick is tender.
Baste if you want during baking.

title: nina's delight(diet)
directions: Mix water with Jell-O.
Mix in fruit and chill.
Cook juice, sugar, flour and eggs until thick.
Mix cream cheese well.
Cool. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over cold Jell-O.

title: cranberry float
directions: Combine the chilled cranberry juice and ginger ale in punch bowl.
Spoon lemon sherbet to cover the surface of the punch. Serve immediately.
Yield:
5 quarts.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix together sugar and eggs first then add the rest of ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: green bean burgers
directions: Add toast to egg and beans.
Add salt and onion.
Spoon into sprayed nonstick skillet.
Makes 2 patties.
Brown on both sides, then top each with 1 slice cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: pecan cheese wafers
directions: Mix cheese and soften well. Combine flour, salt and pepper. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in cereal.
Chill 2 hours.
Shape into balls 1-inch in diameter and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with thumb to 1/2-inch thick.
If using, pecan halves, place half on flattened ball.
If using chopped pecans, stir in mixture before chilling. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen.

title: katherine's shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream together well.
Add cut up shrimp and cut up olives; mix.
Blend in lemon juice, Tabasco and seasoned salt to taste.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and egg with sugar.
Bring water and butter to boil.
Add cocoa and mix.
When cool, add to egg mixture.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° on lowest rack in oven until set.
If pie gets too brown, turn oven temperature down.

title: honey dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in margarine, honey and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on lukewarm water; stir to dissolve. Add yeast, 1 cup flour and eggs to milk mixture.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed until smooth, scraping bowl occasionally.
Or, beat with spoon until batter is smooth. Gradually add enough of the flour to make a soft dough that leaves the sides of the bowl.
Turn out on floured surface and knead until smooth and satiny, about 8 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl; turn over to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Divide dough in half.
Shape into balls; place on greased pan.
Let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan.
Cool on racks.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: spoon bread
directions: Cook grits in 3 cups of water with salt.
Should be soupy. Add meal to hot grits.
When fully mixed, add milk.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in baking powder.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
This dip is very good with raw vegetables.

title: red pepper relish
directions: Wash and remove seeds from bell peppers and grind or chop.
Add all ingredients together.
Boil 1/2 hour.
Put in hot half pint jars.
Seal with lids that have been boiled and are hot.
Put jars in boiling water bath.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 half pints.

title: unbaked bars
directions: Melt peanut butter, margarine and chips.
Cool.
Add marshmallows, nuts and coconut.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: good moist date cake
directions: First cook 1 cup dates and 1/2 cup water for 5 minutes; stir until smooth and thick.
Cool.
Sift together all dry ingredients. Cream shortening, sugar and eggs one at a time, beat well.
Stir in date mixture.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla; add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Can use electric mixer at low speed.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Can use loaf pan or 2 cake pans or Bundt pan with your favorite icing.
(I use creamed cheese icing.)

title: cookies from cake mix
directions: Combine ingredients.
If dough seems too thick, add a little more water.
Roll in balls and bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for approximately 10 minutes.

title: teething biscuits for babies
directions: Mix.
Roll 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut with donut cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover with towel.
Let stand 10 to 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Store in airtight jar.

title: easy yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into a well-greased muffin pan.
Bake at 500° until done.
This mixture will keep in covered dish in the refrigerator for 1 week. If stored in refrigerator, be sure to mix well before putting in muffin pans.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Put the rest of the ingredients in Dutch oven. Add hamburger and chili sauce. Mix all together. Boil 10 to 15 minutes, then let simmer until desired thickness.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cool.
Reserve broth from cooked chicken to use in stuffing instead of water.
Cut chicken up in pieces and layer in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soups together and place over chicken.
Mix stuffing together as directed on box and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: crunchy cheese potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream, milk, chives, salt and pepper. Add potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.

title: blanket pickles
directions: With your fingers, spread each dill pickle with a layer of cream cheese, then wrap with a piece of the ham.
This is especially fun for the little ones because it is so messy to do! But it is just as much fun for them to eat and a healthy alternative.

title: downy cushion rolls
directions: Scald milk; add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm, then add 2 cups of flour, mix well and add well beaten egg.

title: bishop's pie
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into pie pan.
Beat pudding mix, ice cream and milk for 1 minute.
Pour into cooled pie shell. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Top with whipped topping and chocolate curls.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash potatoes; use as many as you need for your family size. Do not peel potatoes. Slice thin. Place in baking dish. Layer potatoes. Slice butter around. Salt and pepper to taste. Layer potatoes and butter until you get what you need. Cover and put in 350° oven about 1 hour, maybe a little longer, depends on how many you have.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces and soak in milk.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and raisins and stir well.
Pour butter in bottom of 11 x 14-inch pan and bake at 350° until very firm.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: cherry delight
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Fold into cherry pie filling. Fold in condensed milk, marshmallows and then sour cream.
Chill at least 8 hours, then serve.

title: barbecue bonanza
directions: At least 6 hours (better if 24 hours) before serving, sprinkle chuck roast with meat tenderizer.
In a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, blend soy sauce with remaining ingredients; refrigerate chuck roast in sauce, turning once.
Grill chuck roast about 5 inches from hot coals for 30 minutes on each side, brushing occasionally with marinade.
Serve with baked potatoes, tossed green salad and toasted French bread.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in beef, minced onion, green pepper, black pepper and sour cream.
Sprinkle on top chopped walnuts or pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Spread on assorted crackers.
May be saved in refrigerator and reheat in microwave.

title: oreo cookie ice cream pie
directions: Soften ice cream and whipped topping.
Set aside.
Crush Oreo cookies and add margarine.
Put cookie mixture in container and spread evenly.
Put and spread ice cream over cookie mixture.
Now spread whipped cream topping over ice cream.
Pour fudge topping over whipped cream.
Now sprinkle some cookie crumbs over and freeze for at least 6 hours.

title: chili casserole
directions: Cook meat until it loses its red color.
Break up with fork. Add next four ingredients.
Stir.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring several times to prevent sticking.
In a 4-quart casserole dish, about 3 1/2-inches deep, layer meat mixture with beans, corn chips, olives and cheese, ending with chips and cheese.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 50 to 60 minutes. Makes 12 generous servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook bacon, onion and green pepper. Drain.
Mix with the remaining ingredients. Serve warm.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar together until sugar dissolves.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Crush the pretzels.
Cream together 3/4 cup butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pour into the pretzel pieces and mix together. Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes and let cool.
Mix the jello with the hot water.
Add strawberries and chill until partially set.
Mix the cream cheese with sugar until creamy.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Spread on the pretzel mix.
Add strawberry mixture as the top layer and chill until ready to serve.

title: taco pie
directions: You will need a round pizza pan and one saucepan.

title: pineapple loaf cake
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Add pineapple and sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites into batter.
Pour
into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: apple dish
directions: Peel and quarter apples.
Lay on crescent dinner rolls. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up.
Place in 9 x 9 baking dish.
In saucepan, heat margarine, orange juice, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle more cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: "goop"
directions: Smooth cream cheese out on bottom of glass or microwavable pan.
Pour can of chili on top of cream cheese, then spread refried beans on top of chili, then sprinkle cheese on top of all of it.
Microwave for 10 minutes.
Serve with chips (Fritos or tortilla chips).

title: slush
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add sugar, pineapple juice and cold water.
Put in freezer; stir occasionally.
When ready to serve, add pop.

title: poultry dressing
directions: Braise onion and celery; add all other ingredients and mix.

title: spiced apple muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add combined egg and milk.
Add shortening and apples.
Pour into greased muffin pans and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased pan 13 x 9 x 2-inches, building up sides slightly.
Bake 10 minutes. Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and eggs; drizzle on top. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until edges are light brown.
Do not overbake.
May be served warm or cold.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Mix cheese, salt and pepper.
Roll potatoes in cheese mixture and put in baking dish with melted margarine.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes.
Potatoes cook faster if covered, about 45 minutes to 1 hour, but uncover last few minutes to brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: green salad
directions: Mix everything in a big bowl with the choice of dressing. Toss until well mixed.
Put into a fancy bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: beans cubano
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add green pepper and garlic. Cook over medium heat, stirring often, 3 to 5 minutes, until pepper is crisp-tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, increase heat and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes, until pepper is tender.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper together.
Layer sliced potatoes in baking dish.
Pour meat mixture over potatoes.
Spread mushroom soup and milk over meat.
Bake in preheated oven 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana boats
directions: Split bananas lengthwise and place in 8 x 8-inch baking dish, cut side up.
Sprinkle brown sugar over bananas.
Dot with butter and scatter nuts on top.
Microwave 1 minute on High or until sugar melts.
Garnish with whipped cream or chocolate syrup, if desired.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins; cool off.
Shred potatoes on big side of grater.
Put shredded cheese and 1/4 cup margarine in saucepan; let it melt.
Remove from stove.
Put sour cream, onions, salt and pepper in.
Fold into potatoes in greased casserole.
Dot with 2 teaspoons margarine; sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Mix ingredients.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake to heat through 325° about 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats; let stand 20 minutes.
Cream the sugars and shortening.
Add oats mixture and eggs.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, and salt.
Beat until well moistened.

title: curried pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Saute onion until tender. Stir in pumpkin, broth, salt, curry powder, nutmeg, pepper, ginger and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Add light cream and stir just until thoroughly heated.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with 1 cup of corn flakes (can substitute with bread crumbs) and 1 stick of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skillet meal
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 25 minutes.

title: pork barbecue sandwich
directions: Place pork roast, water and salt in a Dutch oven. Cover and simmer for 3 1/2 to 4 hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat and shred with 2 forks. Skim fat from pan juices. Stir in celery, steak sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, lemon juice, chili sauce, ketchup and shredded pork. Cover and simmer 1 hour. In a skillet over low heat, saute onions and sugar in oil and butter for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally. Serve pork and onions on bun. A good side is Crumb Coated Potatoes recipe in this book.

title: green salad
directions: Place marshmallows in a bowl. Pour pineapple tidbits over marshmallows and place in refrigerator for 2 or 3 hours. Remove and drain pineapple juice off the marshmallows. Mix pudding mix and Cool Whip in large bowl, then add pineapple and marshmallows to Cool Whip mixture. Add 1/2 cup chopped pecans, if desired.

title: famous pumpkin pie recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix filling ingredients in order given. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue baking 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: irish creme
directions: Blend all the ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.
Shake well before serving.

title: bread pudding and bread pudding sauce
directions: Scald milk, sugar and butter.
Soak bread in this mixture for 5 minutes.
Pour slowly over eggs; add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix together the crab supreme, cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion, Worcestershire sauce and wine.
Chill for 24 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: lime pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add jello; heat until it boils.
Add marshmallows; melt.
Add 1 cup cold water; chill.
Mix cream cheese, pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip.
Add to jello mixture. Allow to set overnight before serving.

title: fancy fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from all fruit.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate 12 hours.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil bouillon and water a little, then add potatoes, celery and onion. Cook 20 minutes or until done. Add California vegetables. Cook 10 minutes slowly. Add chicken soup. Stir and bring to a boil; simmer. Add Velveeta cheese. When cheese is melted, serve. (Don't boil.) Can be frozen. Serves 4 to 5.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese on Warm in microwave, about 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; stir well and heat in microwave on High for about 2 minutes.
Allow to stand for a few minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: egg casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square (1 1/2-quart) baking dish with nonstick spray.
Layer Cheddar cheese, spinach, sausage, mushrooms and green onions in dish.
In medium bowl, combine eggs and half and half; blend well.
Pour egg mixture evenly over layered mixture.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese and paprika.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let set for 5 minutes.

title: fried wontons
directions: Separate wonton
skins.
Place
about
teaspoon
pie filling in the center
of a skin and then roll it up and twist it gently
on
each
end;
fry in hot oil until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper and then dust with powdered sugar.

title: corn chowder
directions: Brown bacon in a large soup pan.
Remove bacon.
To bacon grease, add potatoes and onions and enough water to cook.
When potatoes are done, add corn, milk, soup, salt and pepper.
Turn heat down and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Top servings with the diced bacon.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Cover with corn flakes, mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian pasta bake
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain thoroughly. Cook noodles according to package directions. Saute onions and green peppers. Spray a 13 x 9 x 2 pan with Pam. Combine meat and noodles in pan. Add onions, green peppers and sauce. Mix well. Season to taste. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cathy's ice cream punch
directions: Put ice cream in punch bowl; add Sprite and food coloring. Mix well.

title: spiced tea
directions: Simmer spices, orange and lemon rinds with water for 20 minutes. Remove from heat. Add tea; cover and steep for 3 minutes. Strain. Add fruit juice and sugar. Serve hot or cold.

title: california rolls
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Let stand
for
1/2 hour.
Add eggs, well beaten, flour, salt and melted margarine.
Cover with wax paper and let stand for 3
to
4 hours
to
rise.
Take knife and divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll out
each
part
to
form a thin 13-inch circle. Spread with melted margarine.
Cut in pie shaped pieces (12 in all
from
each circle;
cut
circle
into fourths, then each fourth
into
3 pieces.) Roll up each pie shaped piece, beginning
with
wide edge
and
place on greased pan.
Brush with melted
margarine and
let stand 3 to 4 hours to rise.
Cover with
wax
paper
or place in cold oven to prevent dough from drying out.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add honey, salt and flour. Knead the dough.
Roll into strips and shape into pretzel form. Beat egg and brush on pretzel.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Kids love making these!

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburg and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. (More onion can be added if desired, and 1 pepper could be browned.)
After browning slowly pour in saucepan and add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, couple shakes of chili powder and small amount of catsup.
Simmer this mixture for 1 1/2 hours, very slowly.
Allow 10 sandwiches to 1 pound hamburg.
Worcestershire sauce and chili powder can be used according to how much seasoning desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and zucchini.
Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: In a small saucepan, slowly heat milk and butter.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate, broken into pieces. Stir until chocolate melts.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking soda.
Stir in chocolate mixture until blended.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla until blended.
Stir in egg.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan.
Cool completely on rack.
Frost top and sides with Chocolate Sour Cream Frosting.

title: savory breadsticks
directions: Melt butter in a baking sheet. Blend in bouillon and herbs. Roll breadsticks in mixture and sprinkle with cheese. Bake in preheated 300° oven for 10 minutes. Store in airtight container until ready to serve.

title: liberia spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in alternately with milk and molasses.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in fruit and coconut.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dump cake dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dump in pineapple, swirling it around to fill corners.
Dump in pie filling, pushing it around until layers of fruit are even.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit to cover all.
Melt butter and dribble over top.
Sprinkle nuts over and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is light brown. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip and ice cream.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Blend cheese with 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs and 2 tablespoons vanilla; beat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Fill cupcake papers half full. Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool 5 minutes (center will drop).
Mix 1/4 cup sugar with sour cream and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Fill center of cupcakes, using 1 tablespoon each.
Put back in oven for 7 minutes.
Refrigerate or freeze. Top with preserves.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with crackers on sub buns or as sandwiches.

title: sugar-free lemon pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add yogurt and stir until smooth.
Refrigerate for 15 to 30 minutes, until slightly set. Pour into pie shell and refrigerate until set.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and cool.
After cooled, peel and slice.
Brown bacon and onion.
Remove from grease and put over potatoes.
Add celery salt, salt and pepper.
To grease in pan, add sugar and vinegar and bring to boil.
Shake water and flour and add to pan; when thickened, pour over potatoes and mix.

title: quick company punch
directions: Place on top of punch bowl the ice cream or sherbet.
If serving in glasses, pour pop in glass and top with ice cream or sherbet and slightly mix.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in canister.
Add 1/4 cup to a cup of hot water.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, coconut, egg yolk, nuts and vanilla.
Blend well.
Spread 3/4 of mixture on large shallow pan (jelly roll pan, 11 x 16-inch or larger).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Take out of oven and spread with apricot preserves.
Sprinkle remaining mixture to which 1/4 cup flour has been added (consistency of streusel).
Bake 15 minutes more at 350°.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in ungreased 9-inch pan or casserole dish; set aside.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Spoon batter over peaches.
Combine sugar and water, stirring well. Pour slowly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
In another bowl, mix sour cream and peaches.
Fold dry ingredients into creamed mixture alternately with peach mixture.
Stir in vanilla and almond extracts.
Pour batter into prepared pan; bake at 350° for 75 to 80 minutes.

title: pepperoni crescent rolls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles; stretch slightly.
Place 3 slices pepperoni, slightly overlapping, onto center of each triangle.
Top each with about 1 tablespoon of cheese.
Then roll up, starting with shortest side of triangle and rolling to opposite point.
Place rolls, point side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool off and then dip in sauce and enjoy.

title: cup-a-pizza
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasoning.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Place biscuits in greased muffin tin, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuit-lined cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Yield 12 cups.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight in 1-quart of water in a heavy pot; drain.
Add another 1 1/2 quarts of water, cut up bacon (or ham bone or salt pork), garlic and a little salt.
Simmer slowly 3 or 4 hours until beans are very soft and water has cooked down to a thick red sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste and serve over cooked hot, fluffy rice.
Serves 6.

title: dinosaurwich
directions: Spread the topping about 3/4 of an inch thick on one cookie. Place another cookie on top.
Lightly press edges in garnish. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Serve frozen.
Wrap to store in freezer, up to 2 weeks.
Yields 12.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 6-inch iron skillet or muffin pans.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add vanilla, salt and milk (small amount at a time).
(Mixture will be dry.)
Melt chocolate and wax until it begins to thicken.
Dip cherries in chocolate.
Put on wax paper.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix and boil 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Refrigerate.
Use over chocolate cake and ice cream.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Add oil.
Pour over kraut mixture. Toss lightly. Cover and chill overnight.

title: french silk pie
directions: Use food processor or hand mixer.
Beat butter.
Add sugar. Melt chocolate and add to butter/sugar mixture.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving. Serve with whipped cream and sprinkle with shaved chocolate or cocoa.
Keep refrigerated.
Easy and a favorite with chocolate lovers!

title: macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Cook and drain macaroni as directed on package. Mix together eggs and evaporated milk. Add salt and pepper to taste. Fold in cheese and macaroni. Add milk to make mixture soupy. Pour into casserole dish and dot with margarine. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: mr. lynch's la follette u.m.c.  pancakes
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Beat whole eggs until light and lemon colored.
Add milk.
Fold in flour mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add melted Crisco and vinegar. Bake at 380° on electric frying pan. To prevent sticking, rub pan with paper towel and a few drops of oil or Crisco.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar, butter and vanilla. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture. Blend.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and margarine 2 minutes on High or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate.
Mix in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour and nuts. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, onion, pepper, cheese and bacon.
In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise and sugar together.
Pour over cauliflower mixture.
Mix well. Cover and chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Make a syrup of 1/4 cup of the sugar, 2 tablespoons of the orange juice and 2 tablespoons butter.

title: sons of texas vegetable platter for barbecue
directions: In a 10 1/2 x 14 1/2-inch baking pan, melt 1 tablespoon butter. Coat sides and bottom of pan to prevent sticking.
Arrange vegetables in given order in baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper; top with bacon.
Cover with heavy-duty foil; seal edges. Place vegetable platter on hot part of grill.
Depending on temperature of fire in pit, it usually takes 1 to 1 1/2 hours to cook vegetables until tender.
With a little practice, you will know when to put vegetables on the pit, so they will be ready at the same time as your ribs, chicken, beef or sausage.
Serves 6.

title: snow ball cookies
directions: Combine and mix ingredients.
Chill.
Shape into 1 inch balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
After cooled, shake in powdered sugar.

title: zucchini cakes
directions: Make into patties and fry.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Rinse kraut real good in a strainer. Place in a pot with remaining ingredients. Cook until heated through and serve hot.

title: sauteed scallops with garlic and tomatoes
directions: Notes:
If using sea scallops, cut in half.
If using dried parsley, use 1 tablespoon.

title: low-fat easy spaghetti sauce(9% calories from fat)
directions: Food Processor Directions:
In food processor bowl, with metal blade or blender container, combine all ingredients; process until smooth.
Use as directed in spaghetti.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into greased casserole, covered.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This salad is very good and must be made the day before it is going to be served.
Can be doubled.

title: tangy sweet mustard
directions: Mix vinegar and mustard thoroughly.
Let stand overnight (covered at room temperature for at least 12 hours).
Mix eggs, sugar and salt.
Place all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a slow boil, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and coats a wooden spoon. Cool.
Keeps for months in refrigerator.
This is great on sandwiches or as a dip for cheese cubes and party wieners.

title: heavenly pork chops with milk gravy
directions: Trim pork chops; reserve some pork fat in skillet with tight fitting cover.
Add pork chops to fat; brown on each side.
Drain off excess drippings.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Crush cornflakes slightly; sprinkle over chops.
Cover chops with milk; cover pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Serves 6 or 3 for those who have relatives that like to eat.

title: orange delight
directions: Combine the dry gelatin, cottage cheese, pineapple and mandarin oranges in a bowl and mix well.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Chill thoroughly.

title: pizza on a bagel
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a 9-inch pie plate.
Microwave on High, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in pizza sauce and microwave 1 minute.
Spread sauce evenly on bagel halves.
Top with Mozzarella and grated Parmesan cheese.
Broil 6-inches from heat (with electric oven door partially opened) until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings (85 calories, 1.8 g fat).

title: irish raisin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Stir in sour milk. Form into 2 round loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in two layers.
Prepare pudding, using box directions.
Put 1 layer of cooled cake in large punch bowl. Layer 1/2 of each of the other ingredients on cake, ending with whipped topping.
Repeat beginning with the remaining cake layer. Use large spoon for serving.

title: baked tofu
directions: Mix
all ingredients together in a casserole.
Top with 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 375°.

title: squash balls
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash, then add onion, eggs and salt and pepper to taste.
Make into firm balls and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges well overnight.
Save juice and add sugar.
Beat egg.
Mix flour with egg until smooth.
Add to juice and sugar, whisking until smooth.
Cook until thick and it comes to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cool in refrigerator until quite cold.
Add fruit, pasta and maraschino halves.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, lemon juice and pineapple and pour into crust.
Slice bananas over the pie mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over this.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and sliced cherries. Refrigerate until served.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Knead dough well.
Place in large bowl.
Cover with wax paper and wet towel.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Shape into rolls about the size of a walnut or larger.
Let rise until double.
Bake in preheated oven at 400°. Makes about 30 rolls.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Combine meat, onion, oats, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomatoes. Shape in rolls size of large egg.
Wilt cabbage leaves in hot water.
Roll meat rolls in cabbage leaves.
In 8 x 8-inch casserole, place layer of kraut (1/2 can).
Place meat rolls on top of kraut and cover with rest of kraut and tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook spaghetti.
Boil chicken in water with seasonings.
Save 1 cup water for broth.
Mix together all ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar (a little at a time) and vanilla with a spoon. When finished adding sugar, knead with your hands until well mixed. Roll into balls and set in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour. Melt and cover with chocolate.

title: blueberry crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a round 10 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish or a 10-inch spring-form pan.
In a medium bowl, toss the blueberries with the lemon zest.
In a large bowl, combine 2 cups of the flour with the sugar.
Using your fingertips or a pastry blender, rub or cut in the butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Set 1/2 cup of mixture aside for crumb topping.

title: classic lasagne
directions: In a heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes (put through blender or cut with edge of spoon), paste, sauce, water, salt, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook lasagne as directed; drain.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread about a cupful of sauce, then alternate layers of noodles, sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese, ending with sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until lightly browned and bubbling.
Allow to stand for 15 minutes; cut in squares to serve.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: kidney bean dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve on crackers.
Really good, few calories too.

title: cheese coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in cream; add sugar.
Set aside to ferment. Cut butter into the flour, salt and baking powder; same as for pie crust.
Add egg yolks and the yeast mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add more flour, if necessary to make a soft dough.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll one part to cover the bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: mom's raisin cream pie
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar, flour, salt and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add butter, vanilla and cooked raisins.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Add meringue made from 3 egg whites (beaten) to which 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and 4 tablespoons sugar have been added.
Put in a 350° oven and brown.

title: low-fat dessert
directions: Break angel food cake into pieces and layer in 13 x 9-inch pan or container.
In mixing bowl, mix pudding, as prepared per package directions, with sour cream.
Mix well and pour over cake. Top with can of pie filling or top with some fresh fruit.

title: microwave san francisco chops(makes 4 servings)
directions: Trim pork chops of excess fat.
In a microwave-safe shallow dish (the rounder the shape of the container, the better), combine the oil and garlic.
Spread evenly in dish.
Microwave at High power for 1 minute.

title: carrot salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise and lemon juice together.
Pour over remaining ingredients and combine thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gram's dressing for cabbage
directions: Cook together first 6 ingredients, then cool and add whipped cream.
Pour over grated cabbage to which can of pineapple has been added.
Mix well.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Cook beef, onions and pepper until browned.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, corn, ketchup and chili powder.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove.
Top with corn chips and cheese.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Debone stewed chicken and layer bottom of casserole dish. Pour 3/4 cup of broth from chicken into dish.
Spoon on 1 can of drained, mixed vegetables and cream of chicken soup.
Top with butter, flour and milk mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: dietetic applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Add the applesauce and vanilla.
Sift together the flour and other dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; beat well.
Fold in the raisins and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon onto prepared sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until firm.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: o'brien potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no bake caramel cookies
directions: Put caramels in top of double boiler with 4 tablespoons milk; melt and let cool slightly, then add Rice Krispies, coconut and chopped nuts.
Mix well; roll into balls, flatten and roll in powdered sugar.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread over 11 x 13 pan or pizza pan.
Spread almost all of the cocktail sauce over cream cheese.
Sprinkle shrimp over that.
Then sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate and serve with Club crackers.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Gradually add milk, egg yolk and butter.
Cook on low heat until thick and pour into baked shell or graham cracker crust.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Pour over pie and brown in oven, watching carefully.
Or cool pie and top with whipped cream.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Combine and simmer.
Main dish idea:
Add cut up Polska kielbasa or other cooked sausage and heat up.

title: no bake eskimo cookies
directions: Cream butter; mix in sugar.
Add water, vanilla and cocoa. Mix in oats.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shape into 36 balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Store cookies in refrigerator.
Yield: 36.

title: fluffy sponge cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Blend flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat egg yolks in small mixer bowl until very light and lemon colored.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Beat dry ingredients in alternately (on low speed) with water, flavorings and rind.
In large bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff. Gradually add and gently fold egg yolk mixture into beaten whites. Pour into ungreased tube pan, 10 x 4-inch.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes.
Turn pan upside down with tube over neck of funnel or bottle.
Cool.
Go around pan with serrated knife; pull out, then do the same with bottom.
Wonderful with a cup of tea or after a heavy meal.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa together.
Add 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat egg yolks in 1/2 cup milk. Pour in the milk that's in the pan.
Cook until thickened.
Put in a baked pie crust.
Put 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until stands in peaks.
Add sugar (around 3 or 4 tablespoons) and put on pie.
Brown in oven.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Wash, quarter and remove core from apples.
Pare, if desired, but if red apples are used, skin may be left on to add color. Place apples on cutting board and dice.
Place apples, celery and mayonnaise with salt in mixing bowl; mix lightly.
Add chopped nuts.

title: steamed chinese dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except wonton wrappers) by hand until bound together.
Place one tablespoon mixture in wrapper. Fold square wrapper into triangle and then into another triangles. Place dumplings into steamer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Drizzle with soy sauce.
Makes 50 dumplings.

title: fresh strawberry desert cake
directions: Combine margarine, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla. Line 13 x 9 inch dish with vanilla wafers. Pour cream cheese over wafers; top with sliced strawberries. Top with cool whip and chill overnight.

title: thanksgiving casserole
directions: Stew chicken (slightly salted) until done.
Remove meat from bones and set aside after cutting into medium size pieces.
Melt margarine and add onion and sage.
Stir into dressing.
In a large, greased casserole, begin with a layer of dressing crumbs. Add a layer of chicken, then a can of mushroom soup diluted with 3/4 can of reserved chicken broth.
Again, a layer of crumbs and chicken, then cream of chicken soup diluted with 3/4 can of reserved chicken broth.
Top with crumbs and bake at 350° until done.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening. Stir in yeast and buttermilk. Put in refrigerator and let rise 1 hour. Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter. Let rise 1 hour. Bake in oven at 450° until brown. Makes 40 biscuits.

title: nice and spicy barbecue chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except for chicken.
Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring often.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Crumble bacon over potatoes.
Add onion and cheese. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: tang salad
directions: Drain
and
keep juice from pineapple and oranges.
Mix pudding and Tang.
Add 1 1/2 cup reserved juice.
Do not beat. Add fruit;
