mix gently and chill.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Start hamburger (crumbled) cooking in 1 cup of water. Simmer slowly until done. Add spices. Simmer on top of stove or in crock-pot 2 hours. Then add sugar, tomato puree and ketchup. Simmer 1 more hour; dip off excess fat.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Cut chestnuts in half.
Cut strips of bacon into 3 sections. Wrap section of bacon around half chestnut.
Bake at 350° until crispy (about 30 minutes).
Drain.
Combine ketchup and sugar and pour over chestnuts.
Bake until bubbly (about 10 minutes).

title: monkey pod cake
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in bowl. Roll biscuit pieces in sugar mixture.
Bring to boil butter and brown sugar.
Pour a little syrup mixture in bottom of Bundt pan. Drop
in one can biscuit pieces.
Pour in more syrup and continue alternating until all biscuits are used.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apricot or peach bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
In separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder. Gradually add to butter mixture.
Add coconut, walnuts and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Press 2/3 of dough into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread with preserves; crumble remaining dough over preserves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan on rack.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 36 bars.

title: meme's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, milk, margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla together and beat well.
Bake in casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix corn flakes, brown sugar, pecans and coconut together and sprinkle over the top of casserole.
Brown in oven a few minutes.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: In medium bowl, mix flour and baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple berry salsa
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Coarsely chop apple slices using food chopper.
Dice strawberries and kiwi.
Place fruit in small bowl.
Zest orange to measure 1 teaspoon zest.
Juice orange to measure 2 tablespoons juice.
Add orange zest, juice and brown sugar and jelly to fruit mixture.
Mix gently.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Serve with crackers, cinnamon chips or desired snack.
Makes 3 cups.
Prep time:
15 minutes.

title: pistachio jello salad(watergate salad)
directions: Put pudding mix into a medium size mixing bowl; add crushed pineapple and stir well until jello is dissolved.
Add whipped topping and blend well.
Stir in marshmallows (and coconut, if desired) and stir until well blended.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix chocolate bars, chips, vanilla, Marshmallow Creme and butter in a large bowl and set aside.
Mix sugar and milk in a 4 to 6-quart saucepan and let come to a boil.
Let boil for 10 minutes.
Pour over first mixture and stir.
Add chopped nuts. Pour into Pyrex pan and let stand 4 to 6 hours.
Cut.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Bring ingredients (except egg whites) to a boil.
Cook until it forms a hard ball (5 to 6 minutes).
Beat egg whites stiff. Pour cooked mixture slowly into egg whites while beating.
Drop on greased wax paper.

title: easy christmas cookies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Cook over low heat.
Add food coloring.
Add corn flakes; stir into mixture.
Shape mixture into wreaths on waxed paper.
Decorate wreaths with cinnamon hearts. Cool in refrigerator to harden.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add 1 cup milk and yolks and mix.
Add the rest of the milk.
Cook between low and medium stirring constantly until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Top with your favorite meringue and brown.

title: kentucky bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Warm sweet potatoes in a large saucepan.
Mash with electric mixture.
Add sugar, bourbon, margarine and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Turn mixture into shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake uncovered at 350° until marshmallows are golden.

title: cream taffy
directions: Combine all ingredients, except gelatin.
Boil to a hard ball. Soak gelatin in cold water and add.
Remove from heat and cool. Then it is ready to pull; add vanilla.

title: farfalle ai pignoli con lemone(easy sauce while pasta cooks)
directions: Boil 5 quarts water in a large pot.
In a double boiler, melt the butter.
Stir in the pignoli nuts or walnuts, lemon zest and dry vermouth or cognac.
Maintain at low heat until pasta is ready (al dente).
Drain the pasta and place in a serving bowl.
Add the sauce and serve with grated riggiano, parmesiano and cracked pepper.
Guests will rave.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix milk, oats, butter, salt and brown sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Combine yeast and water. Stir in oat mixture.
Mix with eggs and flour and let stand 1 hour.
Punch down.
Divide in 2 loaves.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, sugars and egg.
Add flour, baking powder and soda.
Chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into small balls, then flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake in Bundt pan at 250° for 2 hours.

title: slaw
directions: Prepare all vegetables; drain the raisins and mix all together in a large bowl.
Mix brown sugar, Italian dressing and salad dressing mix together. Stir to dissolve. Pour over slaw just before serving. Serves 50.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, cut margarine into flour until a crumb mixture forms.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes; cool.
Beat powdered sugar with cream cheese until light and fluffy; fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Spread over powdered sugar layer. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with nuts; refrigerate until serving time.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar and butter.
Cook over medium heat until thick (about 30 minutes) and stirring often.
Add vanilla and raisins. Serve hot or cold.

title: veal with mushrooms and white wine
directions: Pound veal cutlets and dredge in flour.
Heat large frying pan over medium heat; put in oil.
Drop in cutlets, salt and pepper to taste and cook, turning over at least 1 to 2 times.
Add minced garlic and butter and cook a few more minutes.
Then add sliced mushrooms, covering cutlets.
Add wine and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Liquid will reduce down; you may need to add more wine.
Salt and pepper again to taste.

title: chinese shrimp salad
directions: Cook noodles as per package directions, and drain.
Add mayonnaise	and
dry
Ranch
dressing mix. Toss with remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Brown and partially cook chicken in frypan.
Combine all ingredients except chicken and cook in saucepan until thick.
Put chicken in roasting pan and pour sauce over and cover.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart dish.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Stir in bread and raisins.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Put in dish.
Put water in pan to reach halfway up on sides of dish.
Bake until knife comes out clean, about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, green pepper and seasonings to taste. Simmer.

title: chicken to go biscuits
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, all at once, and cook about 1 minute, until thickened.
Stir in chicken, cheese and mushrooms.

title: barbecue hog rinds
directions: Take plain bag of hog rinds and dip them in bowl of barbecue sauce.

title: pork chops with apples and stuffing
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops in oil over medium-high heat. Meanwhile, prepare stuffing according to package directions. Spread pie filling that has been mixed with the cinnamon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place the pork chops on top; spoon stuffing over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes longer.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: augratin potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes with skins on.
Put in pot with onions bacon and seasonings.
Cover with water.
Boil until potatoes are soft.
Pour off excess water.
In cake pan or large baking dish, add a layer of potatoes, salt and pepper, spoonfuls of butter and cheese.
Repeat several times.
Bake at 350° until butter and cheese are melted. Serve hot.

title: maple acorn squash
directions: Cut acorn squash in half.
Scoop out seeds and fill 3/4 of each side with pancake syrup and top each side with a pat of butter.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to
1 hour.

title: cider pineapple special
directions: Pour fruit juices into a 2-quart pan.
Add mint and bring to a boil.
Strain.
Bring to a boil again.
Add ginger ale and serve at once.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Combine with all other ingredients and mix well.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
After frozen, store in plastic bag in freezer.
To serve, bake frozen for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter dessert
directions: In a bowl, combine the crushed cookies, sugar and butter; press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, bottom only. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.

title: pink cloud dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then fold in Dream Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: To frost grapes, dip in slightly beaten egg whites.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Allow to dry on wire rack.

title: jane's onion rings
directions: Mix ingredients.
Coat onions.
Cook, not touching each other, until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: crab salad
directions: Cut crab into bite-sized pieces.
Mix with salad and the amount of dressing you desire.

title: mama e's hushpuppies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
More buttermilk can be added if the mixture is too thick.
Drop by small spoonfuls and deep fry in hot oil until hushpuppies are brown.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Add sugar and yeast to warm water.
Let stand 30 minutes. Blend dry ingredients.
Add butter and honey.
Add yeast mixture while mixing on low speed.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Knead dough. Roll into pie type flat dough.
Cut into 3 x 2-inch squares.
Cook in deep fat at 375°.
After placing dough in hot fat, punch once so dough goes below level of fat.
Remove when golden.
Drain and serve with honey.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix sour cream, milk and Tang thoroughly.
Stir in Cool Whip. Pour in two graham cracker crusts.
Garnish with mandarin oranges, if desired.
Chill and serve.
Will freeze.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 2 1/2 minutes. Start counting time when mix reaches full, rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat well until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti noodles.
Mix noodles, large, diced tomato, diced cucumber, 1 bottle dressing and salad seasoning. Chill.
Serve.

title: lemon strawberry punch
directions: Stir first three ingredients together in punch bowl.
Pour in liquids.
Add ice.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter into skillet.
Add flour.
Brown slightly.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery.
Saute until wilted.
Add crawfish tails.
Add one cup of warm water to the skillet.
Add Season-All or salt and pepper to taste.
Cook approximately 40 minutes on low heat.
Serve over white or brown rice.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt butter and sugar together.
Add cocoa, flour, unbeaten eggs, vanilla and nuts; mix.
Pour into greased pie pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cover broccoli with water and cook about 4 minutes; set aside. Put butter and flour in a pan with minced onion.
Saute onion and then add milk.
Cook until it boils.
Then add cooked broccoli and 1 cup juice left over from boiling the broccoli.
Then add seasonings (lemon juice, lemon rind, cheese, salt and pepper).
If soup appears too thick, add more of the broccoli liquid.
Heat and serve.
Ham or bacon bits can be added for flavor or leave plain. Makes 6 servings.

title: apple dabble
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: overnight layered chicken salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Spread lettuce evenly in a shallow 4-quart serving dish.
Top with bean sprouts, water chestnuts, nuts, onion, cucumber and chicken.
Pat pea pods dry and arrange on top.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased and floured, rectangular cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread with icing while hot.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Use metal saucepan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Place well-rinsed, unpeeled shrimp in pan.
Put all vegetables and fruit on top of shrimp.
Melt oleo.
Add seasoning.
Pour over shrimp and vegetables.

title: duck bread
directions: I asked my daughter what her favorite bread is and she said "Duck Bread."
I asked her how to make it and this is what she said:
"Duck Bread:
You tear it apart and throw it to the ducks."

title: potato-caramel cake
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar; add egg yolks, spices, chocolate and
hot
potatoes.
Sift dry ingredients together; save enough to dredge nuts and raisins.
Beginning with flour; add flour
and milk
alternately.
Fold
in
egg whites, nuts and raisins.
Bake at
to 350° in 2 square layer pans.
Use caramel
icing between
layers
and over cake.
Store in air-proof tin.
Tastes better when aged a while.

title: sausage-hamburger supreme
directions: Cook sausage in a pan and drain.
Cook hamburger in a separate pan and drain.
Add the 2 meats and brown together.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Serve just like a hamburger on buns or roll.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs, strawberries and oil and add the dry ingredients.
Add pecans.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Use 3 small loaf pans.
If using small tins, bake 37 minutes.

title: no bake brownie mix cookies
directions: Combine first three ingredients and bring to a rolling boil for two minutes while stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on to wax paper and serve when cool.

title: steak and pepper stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in hot skillet.
Add onions and garlic; cook 3 minutes.
Add ginger, peppers and broccoli; cook 5 minutes, adding meat after 2 minutes.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients; add to pan.
Cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix together butter, Worcestershire sauce, oil, garlic salt, red pepper, liquid smoke, Accent, chili powder and sugar. Heat until butter is melted. Then pour over cereal mixture and stir to mix well. Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes. Store in a sealed container or jar.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Fold in the strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts all at once. Place half of mixture into mold.
Chill until firm (at least 1 hour).
Leave remaining mixture at room temperature.
Spread sour cream on chilled half.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Chill until firm.
May be served on lettuce leaf.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and store in jar in refrigerator.
Use for oysters, clams, shrimp, crabmeat or lobster.
Yield: About 1 cup.

title: graham cracker delights
directions: Boil together the butter, sugar, egg and milk for 1 minute. Add nuts, coconut and crumbs.
Place layer of graham crackers in pan, face side up.
Spread mixture over crackers.
Put whole crackers on top.
Spread icing over graham crackers.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Stir in flour and sugar together.
Then stir into milk.
Melt margarine in bottom of baking dish.
Let sizzle.
Pour batter into melted margarine, then pour fruit on top.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mints
directions: Mix margarine, syrup and flavor; add sugar and mix well. Mixture will be crumbly but continue to work until it becomes smooth.
"Must air 24 to 48 hours."

title: mama's recipe for pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in 2-quart bowl.
Stir in sugar, syrup and melted margarine.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes until filling is slightly firm.
Center of pie will become firm when cool.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: In a large 3 to 4-inch deep frying pan, heat the oil to 375°. In a wide mixing bowl or soup bowl, combine the bread crumbs, cornmeal, cayenne pepper, salt and black pepper.

Slice the tomatoes about 1/2-inch thick. Sprinkle the Tabasco sauce over the tomatoes. Lightly dust the tomatoes with the flour. Dip the tomato slices into the egg whites and then into the bread crumb mixture. Make sure the tomatoes are well coated on all sides.
Fry in hot oil for 4 minutes on each side. Drain on paper towels.

title: bean soup
directions: Place beans in large pot and let heat.
Brown ground meat in skillet.
Saute onion and add meat and onion to beans.
Simmer for about an hour.
Serve with cornbread and green salad.

title: smoked rib-eye loin
directions: Roll loin in salt and pepper until it is covered.
Place in smoker on ideal heat for 5 hours (30 minutes for each pound).

title: tunnel of cheese muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine biscuit mix and bacon.
Add milk and egg, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon half of batter into buttered 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Press a cheese cube into each cup.
Top with remaining batter, covering cheese completely.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pan.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: oven-baked potatoes
directions: While preheating oven to 350° to 400°, melt butter in large Pyrex dish.
Peel and cut potatoes into wedges.
Coat potatoes in a bag with flour.
Place potatoes in Pyrex dish with butter and stir until all are coated well.
Cook for approximately 45 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes and marshmallows
directions: Peel sweet potatoes.
Boil in salted water until soft.
Drain and mash with butter or margarine; season to taste.
Spread in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish (greased).

title: butterfly bites
directions: Cut celery stalks in half, crosswise.
Fill each with cheese. Add 2 pretzel wings on each side.
Use pretzel pieces for antennae and raisins for decorating body.

title: easy chocolate frosting
directions: Blend dry ingredients in saucepan.
Slowly mix in water.
Heat while stirring until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and margarine.
Let cool before use.

title: homemade bread
directions: Use no salt.
Mix flour and lard together until well blended. Put yeast in warm water; add to flour mixture.
Add sugar.
Mix together until well blended.
Put flour onto table.
Put flour mixture onto it.
Knead dough 250 times or until it snaps back. Let raise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Let rise again for same time. Put into pans.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 330° for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Combine wet ingredients in one bowl, dry in another.
Then mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a small casserole dish.
Skin and bone chicken breasts.
Salt and pepper chicken.
In a small skillet, brown chicken in margarine.
After browning, place in casserole along with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla wafers, alternating with milk.
Add coconut and mix together well. Pour mixture into a greased and floured tube pan with wax paper. Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line unbaked pie shell with 1/2 of cheese. Top cheese with cooked sausage. Cover with remaining cheese.

title: mom's vegetable soup
directions: In a large pan put the Water, Salt, Vegetable Oil, Thyme and Pepper bringing to a boil.
Add the Celery and Carrots; let boil for 5 minutes.
Add the Green Pepper, Onion, Whole Tomatoes cut up, Sugar and Tomato Sauce; let boil 5 more minutes.
Then add Spaghetti.
Add the two or either one of the two optional ingredients.
It is delicious and gives you a whole meal in one pan.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Beat together good cream cheese and sugar.
Add drained, crushed pineapple and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip and sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: tempeh chili
directions: Grate tempeh
and marinate in next 5 ingredients for 1 hour. Heat next five ingredients in a large saucepan.
Add green pepper and onion for 5 minutes.
Add tempeh with marinade for 5 minutes. Add remainder of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves 6.
Cooking time is 1 hour, not including marinating time.

title: dobo stew
directions: Brown meat with onion.
In large Dutch oven or crockpot, combine all other ingredients and stir.
Let simmer.

title: teriyaki meat balls
directions: Combine soy sauc with sugar, onion, garlic powder and ginger. Let stand 10 minutes.
In bowl, mix meat and crumbs; stir in soy sauce.
Shape into 3/4-inch meat balls.
Place meat balls 1/2 inch apart in pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Made additional soy sauce recipe to pour over meat balls, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Cover so meat balls will not dry out or keep basting with soy sauce.
Serve with wild rice.
Delicious!

title: strawberry cake(terry's favorite)
directions: Mix cake mix with 1/2 box strawberries and 4 egg yolks. Mix hot water with gelatin
and
add
to
cake mix.
Add salad oil, blend well.
Beat egg
whites
until
stiff and fold into batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour,
in
2 or 3 layer cake pans. Put 1 layer on cake
plate
and
put 3/4 box strawberries over layer, then add frosting.
Add second layer of cake and repeat with strawberries and frosting.
Add third layer if you used 3 pans and frost over sides
and top.
Use White Mountain Frosting recipe.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour and beef broth.
Stir vigorously with wire whisk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add milk and potatoes.
Crumble fried bacon in soup.
Let simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until ready to serve.
This will keep well for several days.

title: lo-cal vanilla ice cream
directions: In stainless steel or heatproof glass bowl or top of double boiler, beat egg yolks and sugar together until thick and creamy. In a saucepan, scald 1 cup milk, add vanilla and pour over the eggs; mix well.
Stir slowly and continually over a saucepan of simmering water until thickened slightly, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat, pour in remaining milk; cool.
Pour into ice cream canister.
Freeze in maker according to directions.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
May double recipe.

title: easy garden bake
directions: Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese evenly in pan. Beat Bisquick, eggs, milk and spices until smooth with mixer.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400° in 8 x 8-inch square lightly oiled pan until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender at high speed for 30 seconds. Pour into buttered pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and meat.
Make small balls.
Heat sauce and jelly to boiling.
Add meat balls.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes.

title: tomato stuffed potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Scoop out and reserve shells.
Mix potato with other ingredients, except cheese.
Return to potato shells.
Top with cheese.
Place in conventional or microwave oven until hot and cheese is melted.
Makes 8 stuffed potato halves.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Pour dressing over chicken with onion soup.
Mix well, cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serve with rice and Italian string beans.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat; add grated white chocolate.
Stir until chocolate melts. Set aside; let cool to room temperature.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt in a large bowl; beat at medium speed until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add cooled white chocolate mixture; mix well. Add flour, beating until smooth.
Stir in chopped chocolate and vanilla.
Spread batter in a greased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into squares. Yields 16 brownies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; stir in sugar, corn syrup and softened or melted butter.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Center of pie may look soft when pie is gently shaken, but will firm when cool.

title: pork and beans casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Mix remainder of liquids with beef.
Mix together and bake in an ungreased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into small pieces and simmer, covered, until tender (for approximately 6 to 8 minutes) in a small amount of boiling water.
Shake the pan to keep the squash from sticking.
Drain well.
In a separate pan, combine yogurt, butter, grated cheese and paprika.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat and stir in beaten egg yolk and chopped chives.
Add the squash.
Place the mixture in a baking dish and top with buttered bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Serves 4.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Saute chopped onion, garlic, spices and chicken in large pot containing olive oil, stirring well to coat chicken.
Then cover and cook slowly, about 20 minutes.
Add tomato paste and water, stir well.
Cook over medium heat, partially covered, until sauce is thick and chicken is tender, about 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: slim jim chili
directions: Brown meat and onion in a large frypan or Dutch oven; drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer, covered, for one to two hours.

title: nitey nite cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar slowly and beat until stiff.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a foiled covered cookie sheet.
Place in oven heated to 375°.
Turn oven off and leave until morning.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a lightly greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish, stirring well.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Yields 8 servings.

title: very easy banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding, milk and condensed milk. Fold in the whipped topping. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas, and pudding mixture. Repeat layers. top with whipped topping or crushed vanilla wafers.

title: apricot cream cheese cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Blend in eggs, lemon juice and rind.
Add combined ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Shape level tablespoonfuls of dough into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Indent centers; fill with preserves. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: fudge oatmeal cookies(no bake)
directions: Have all ingredients measured and ready to use.
Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Add milk; bring to a boil. Add peanut butter and butter.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal (and nuts). Drop on waxed paper (tablespoonful).
Cool.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and pineapple. Pour in casserole.	Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered, or until knife comes out clean when inserted.

title: apple drink
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine all ingredients and mix with mixer until well mixed and mostly smooth.
Put in foil lined cupcake tins (fill 1/2 way).
Bake for 45 minutes.
While baking, combine 8 ounces sour cream, 2 teaspoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove cupcakes when done and allow to sit out on counter in pan about 5 minutes or until center sinks.
Put a teaspoonful of sour cream mixture on top of each cupcake.
Return to oven.
Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Store in refrigerator.
Tastes better the 2nd day.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavoring to milk.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder; add milk and flour mixture to egg mixture.
Pour into well greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer (until thick).

title: green pea casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in margarine until tender, but do not brown.
Add peas, chestnuts and pimentos.
Add mushroom soup to mixture and place in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with Ritz or cheese cracker crumbs.
Place in 250° oven and allow to just bubble. Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, water, syrup, peanuts and salt in a 2-quart bowl or casserole.
Cook on High in microwave 5 minutes, then stir.
Cook on High 13 to 15 minutes or until syrup separates into threads.
This is hard crack stage or 300° on a candy thermometer. Stir in butter, baking soda and vanilla just until light and bubbly.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet and spread.
Cool and break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: quick applesauce crisp
directions: Combine applesauce, raisins, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Turn into a 9 inch pan.
Mix biscuit mix, sugar and butter. Sprinkle over the applesauce and bake 25 minutes in 325° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and shape into ball.
Chill and roll ball in 1 cup chopped pecans until evenly coated with nuts. Chill.
Serve with Ritz or Town House crackers.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Blend into first mixture.
Make into roll and chill overnight.
Cut thin; sprinkle with sugar and bake until slightly brown in moderate oven 10 minutes.
(Do not grease cookie sheet.)

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels and margarine and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Then fold in 2 cups frozen nondairy whipped topping.
Spread over cooled pretzel mixture.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Heat oven
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or two round 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch layer pans.
Measure all ingredients
into a large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed,
scraping
bowl
constantly.
Beat
minutes
on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Frost, if desired.

title: clingons-cereal treat
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large microwave-safe bowl, melt 4 cups marshmallows, peanut butter and margarine on High for 2 minutes or until melted.
Stir until smooth.
In the following order, add remaining 1/2 cup marshmallows, Rice Chex, M&M's and Corn Chex to melted mixture.
Spread mixture evenly into prepared pan with back of a buttered spoon.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Pull apart and enjoy!
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: corn chowder
directions: Mix liquids and butter, add potatoes and onions, cook until done. Mix cracker crumbs, flour and seasonings. Add to potatoes and onion mixture. Add bell peppers, mix well, bring to a boil, add half & half and corn, Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Chill. Roll into balls.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix pudding mix with fruit cocktail.
Add pineapple and fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate in serving bowl until set.
Serves 10. Approximate calories per serving:

title: applesauce cake
directions: On a piece of waxed paper sift together the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves.
In a large mixing bowl cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in sifted flour mixture in 4 additions alternately with applesauce, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Mix the raisins and walnuts with the last addition of flour, and stir in.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Place grated zucchini in colander; squeeze out as much liquid as possible.
Mix the zucchini with eggs and onion in large bowl. In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt and oregano. Stir in grated zucchini mixture.

title: mixed green salad and salad dressing
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar and oil together.
Cool.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Cool and crumble.
Tear salad greens in pieces in large bowl.
Slice onion thin and separate into rings.
Add mushrooms. Add bacon.

title: farm cookies
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Sift; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter for 30 seconds.
Add sugars; beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla; add the flour mixture.
Beat until combined.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Flatten slightly with a glass.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
You can add raisins and/or chocolate chips.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add 7-Up alternately with flour.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extract. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Better results are obtained when ingredients are at room temperature.

title: health cookies
directions: Cream oleo, brown sugar and egg.
Add vanilla, grated carrot, pecans and raisins.
Blend in well.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to batter and mix well.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: "candy cane" oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter and vanilla until creamy.
Add sugar gradually; beat until fluffy.
Add water.
Sift together flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in oats until blended. Dough will be stiff.
Shape into canes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Frost canes with thin confectioners sugar icing.
Stripe with thick red frosting.
Makes 36, depending on the size of the canes.

title: fried pies(home dried apples or peaches are best)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, place flour and margarine.
Mix to a coarse meal texture.
Add enough cold water, small amount at a time, and stir with fork until all flour sticks together.
Flour hands and place dough on floured biscuit board or cloth.
Knead 8 or 10 times until firm and smooth.
Place dough back in bowl. Pinch off egg size dough.
Roll thin on floured board.
Place saucer or small plate over rolled dough.
Trim edges, will be round, and place 2 tablespoons fruit, sweetener, on rolled dough. Fold over crimp edge with fork.
Put 2 tablespoons of oil in heavy skillet on medium heat.
Place 2 pies in hot oil.
Brown.
Turn and brown other side.
Makes 12 pies.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar and oleo. Stir in flour and baking powder. Add milk and coconut. Pour into pie plate that has been sprayed with Pam. Fill full (does not cook over). Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In blender, add Karo, butter, salt, egg, sugar and vanilla. Blend well.
Place pecans in bottom of pie crust, pour mixture over nuts.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Then chop.
Beat eggs and mix with mayonnaise. Mix broccoli and cheese with egg, mayonnaise and soup.
Melt butter in pan.
Add cracker crumbs.

title: cake icing
directions: In large bowl, add all ingredients and mix (I mix by hand). Add vanilla.
Spread on cooled Duncan Hines sheet cake.
Sprinkle top with coconut or finely chopped nuts.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain. Add beans and soup. Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased dish. Drop mounds of mashed potatoes and sprinkle with processed cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 6.

title: coffeecake
directions: Mix liquids and dry separately, then put together and mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch square or round pan, greased. Sprinkle top with a pinch of flour, good amount brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: shirley's chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Then add Cool Whip to pudding.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Add 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Make another layer of graham crackers, then add rest of pudding mixture.
Then add one last layer of whole graham crackers.

title: cinderella's fantasy crepes
directions: Combine eggs, flour, salt and 1 cup milk; beat until smooth. Let stand 30 minutes.
Pout 1/4 cup batter into hot lightly greased 8-inch skillet.
Cook until underside is lightly browned.
Saute vegetables in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add 1 cup milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese, stir until melted.
Stir in chicken or ham.
Fill each crepe with mixture (1/4 cup).
Roll up and place crepes in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: rice-broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Pour hot water over the broccoli; let stand for 5 minutes. Drain well.
Mix all ingredients.
Make 1 large or 2 small casseroles.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
If frozen, be sure to allow more time for baking.

title: funeral cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions; while warm, poke holes in cake top using wooden spoon.
Pour Caramel topping over cake top, let cool completely.
Sprinkle 1/2 of heath bars over cake; spread cool whip over top; sprinkle with remaining heath bars.
Chill until set.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk in bowl.
Then pour batter over butter.
Do not stir.
Spoon peaches over batter.
Bake for 1 hour or until brown.

title: honey buns
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
In a small bowl, combine nuts, honey and 1/3 cup melted oleo.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.

title: golden glow pickles
directions: Boil until transparent; put in jars.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and sugar and mix well.
Put in the pie shell.
Put topping on and refrigerate until serving.

title: brenda's salad
directions: Pour all drained fruits together into bowl.
Add bananas. Mix in enough cool whip to desired consistency.

title: meat loaf
directions: Dissolve soup mix in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place ingredients in a loaf pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: pretty pear salad
directions: Place lettuce leaf in bowl.
Place pear on lettuce leaf.
Fill pear center with cottage cheese.
Put cherry on top.
Makes one serving.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar gradually.
Beat until light and fluffy and sugar is dissolved.
Add egg yolks, beating well.
Combine buttermilk and soda; stir until soda is dissolved. Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Add 1 1/2 cups walnuts and coconut, stirring well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard to make sauce.
Mix 1/2 cup sauce, meat, egg, onion, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper well.
Shape in loaf pan.
Top with remaining sauce. Do not cover.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: club woman cake
directions: Mix together.
Spread over slightly cooled cake.
Place in hot oven until frosting is brown.

title: "ritzy" chicken
directions: Blenderize Ritz crackers until fine crumbs. Mix in seasonings. Wash and take skin off chicken.
Line two 9 x 13-inch pans with aluminum foil. Dip chicken pieces in melted butter to coat and then in Ritz crumbs.
Place in foil lined pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Add shortening and sugar together and beat.
Beat eggs and add.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add.
Stir in coconut and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Make balls size of walnut; put on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork lengthwise.
Bake at 375°.

title: lo-fat pasta salad
directions: Do not overcook noodles, should still be firm in center; rinse well with cold water.
Prepare Italian dressing.
Use a high grade vinegar for best result.
Mix all salad ingredients in a large bowl.
This makes a large salad.
Pour dressing over salad ingredients and toss.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice; blend well. Mix all dry ingredients together and gradually add to pumpkin mixture. Pour/spread evenly into jelly roll pan that has been greased well and floured. Bake 12 minutes at 375°. Invert cake onto towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Roll up in towel and cool cake completely.

title: purple jello punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix sugar.
Add water, Kool-Aid and juice; mix well.
Freeze, stirring occasionally.
Add lemon-lime soda just before serving.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine soup, vegetables, sour cream, pepper, half of Swiss cheese and half of onion rings.
Put in 1-quart casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Steam raisins, let cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix 1 cup flour with fruits, nuts and coconut. Add sifted dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Mix well and add fruit and nuts to batter.
Drop by spoon on greased baking sheet. Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.
This makes a lot of cookies.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Mix all
together.
Place in buttered 1 1/2 quart baking dish. Then
place baking dish in pan of hot water.
Bake until knife inserted
1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with or without hard sauce or cream.

title: crab meat and pasta salad
directions: Make a day before use.

title: banana cream cheese roll
directions: Mix or beat eggs, sugar and banana well; add in salt, flour and baking soda.
Grease and flour an 11 x 12-inch cookie sheet or one size larger.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Loosen with spatula. Roll and cool 20 minutes.

title: cake doughnuts
directions: Use enough flour to make a soft dough. Cream together butter and sugar. Add rest of ingredients. Roll and cut; fry in deep fat. Sugar while hot.

title: heavenly angel cake
directions: Bake cake and cool.
Mix together milk, lemon juice and almond extract.
Cut peaches into bite size pieces.
When cake is cold, slice off top about 1-inch thick.
Put to one side; be careful not to break apart.
With sharp knife, cut down and around cake and carefully scoop out, leaving a trench.
Combine whipped topping with first mixture and divide in half.
To one half, add broken up cake pieces and peaches.
Stuff into cake and replace top.
Ice cake with remainder of mixture.
Decorate with peach slices. Refrigerate immediately.

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil the sugar and Karo syrup for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs separately.
Pour eggs into syrup, stirring constantly.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add all other ingredients in a 10-quart pan; bring to a boil and lower heat to medium for 30 minutes.

title: tasty pizza snacks
directions: Take casings off sausage as needed. Crumble into large skillet. Brown. Add onions and green pepper. Cook until browned and done. Drain well. Blot with paper towel. Heat on low. Add cheese and seasonings. Heat until melted. Keep warm. Put 1 tablespoon onto bread and spread. Freeze on a cookie sheet and then transfer to a Ziploc bag. You can then get out a few without them "sticking together". Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes a bunch of appetizers.

title: peanut pudding cake
directions: Blend flour and margarine with a pastry cutter or fork.
Add 2/3 cup peanuts.
Pat into a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: exotic casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups water with bouillon cubes.
Clean and cook shrimp.
Brown following ingredients in skillet:
ham, onion, garlic and salad oil.
Blend together soy sauce, curry powder, ginger and salt.
Add sauce mixture to ham mixture with green pepper cut in strips.
Cut shrimp and add.
Add 4 slices of pineapple, cubed.
Heat through.
Toss mixture with cooked rice and place in greased casserole.
Heat in oven at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: mandarin pancakes
directions: Mix together the boiling water and flour.
Mix with a spoon. Add cold water and knead dough.
Shape dough into long tube and cut off pieces the equivalent of 2 tablespoons. Keep pieces you are not working covered with plastic wrap to keep from drying. Take one piece and flatten with hands.
Place it on a lightly floured board and roll it thin.

Brush one side of two rolled pancakes with seasame oil and place the two oiled sides together facing each other. Roll thinner. Cook both sides on lightly oiled surface (wok or skillet) until lightly browned.
Remove and separate the pancakes. Set aside under a slightly damp cloth until all are done.
You may wish to steam the pancakes before serving to warm.
Use like a tortilla for Mu Shoo Pork or anything you might use a crepe for (great with fruit).
The sesame oil adds a great aroma.

title: prime rib
directions: Line large roasting pan with foil, extending foil about 12-inches on each end to fold over later.
Pour 1-inch rock salt in bottom pan, covering entire bottom.
Place roast in pan.
Pour Worcestershire sauce over roast.
Encase roast with rock salt so that entire roast is covered by 1-inch salt.
Fold over foil to cover completely.
Put in hot oven (500°) for 22 minutes per pound (4 pounds equals 88 minutes, medium-rare).
Remove and scrape off all salt.
Slice and broil (if desired) for 1 minute.

title: vegetable cheese casserole
directions: Combine frozen vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Top with rest of cheese and onions and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine in a 2-quart casserole the sugar, syrup and salt. Microwave 5 minutes on High.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes to brown.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Add butter, vanilla and soda.
Stir until light and foamy.
Spread on well-buttered cooking sheet.
Cool.
Break in pieces.

title: fudge balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Into a large bowl, sift together the flour, sugar and salt.
Add the butter, chocolate and coffee, beating well until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Fold in the rolled oats.

title: chicken salad bake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice and salt.
Cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover.
Continue to bake until thickened and bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Serve in baking dish alone or over rice. Also delicious on sandwiches cold the next day.

title: strawberry and cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple tidbits and set aside.
Completely thaw Cool Whip.
Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add Jell-O mix (dry). Mix well and add pineapple, thoroughly mix.
Chill and serve.

title: brownie gems
directions: Bake in cupcake cups in 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Melt margarine and chocolate in bowl, the batter will be mixed in.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add nuts.
Pour into cupcake cups and bake 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; break into 2-inch pieces.
Combine cooked spaghetti with oleo, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and egg; set aside.
Brown hamburger with onion, green pepper, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Add to this the spaghetti sauce.
Cream together the cottage cheese, parsley and seasoned salt.
Line a 9 x 12-inch pan with half of spaghetti, half of sauce mixture, then all of cottage cheese mixture.
Add remaining spaghetti mixture.
Top with rest of the sauce.
Sprinkle 4 ounces of Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
You can make a day ahead and refrigerate, but allow more cooking time.

title: tart lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, egg yolks and flour/cornstarch; mix well.
Stir in can of evaporated milk and water.
Cook slowly over low heat until it thickens.
Add lemon juice and pour into baked pie crust. Top with meringue and bake until browned at 350°.

title: french onion bread
directions: Soften dry yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Combine soup mix and 2 cups water.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Add sugar, salt, cheese and shortening; stir.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups of the flour; beat well.
Stir in yeast.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic (8 to 10 minutes).
Place in a lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover; let double in a warm place (1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down; divide in half.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 long loaves, tapering ends.
Place on greased baking sheet sprinkled with corn meal.
Gash tops diagonally, about 1/4-inch deep.
Cover.
Let double (about 1 hour).
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 20 minutes.
Brush with mixture of 1 egg white and 1 tablespoon _____.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until done.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Blend together and roll into pencil like crescents.
Bake at 300° until done.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: green tomato relish(chow-chow)
directions: Grind tomatoes;
drain well.
Grind onions and peppers; mix together with
well
drained tomatoes.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Cook 45 minutes on medium heat.
Put into clean hot jars and seal at once.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crush Doritos and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain off fat.
Add both cans of soup.
Heat all ingredients and pour over Doritos.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions and pepper in skillet.
Mix beans, Ro-Tel and chicken soup together in a large bowl.
Grease bottom of casserole dish.
Place uncooked tortillas in bottom of dish.
Layer meat, beans, Ro-Tel and soup.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Place layer of tortilla shells on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: big bucket in the sky chicken
directions: In a greased pan, arrange chicken, skin side up.
Melt 1/4 pound margarine.
Brush or drizzle on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 45 minutes, until brown.

title: cheese soup
directions: Put cheese and milk on low heat; melt and stir.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add to cheese and half and half mixture. In a large stock pot, boil cauliflower and broccoli until tender. Add noodles, macaroni, garlic powder and chicken bouillon together.
Cook until macaroni is done.
Add ingredients in stock pot to cheese.
Warm; don't cook much longer (only warm).

title: cola coolers
directions: Divide ice between 8 tall glasses.
Pour 2 tablespoons syrup over ice in each glass.
Fill glasses with carbonated beverage. Stir.
Serve with straws, if desired.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and pulp together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add melted butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Leave in pan until cool.
Cut in squares.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Sift baking powder, salt and rest of the flour.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with blueberries.
Let stand 1 hour.
Combine the two mixtures alternately with the flour.
Add the floured berries last.
Bake in buttered tin gem pans about 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine shortening, peanut butter, both sugars and vanilla. Mix in eggs.
Combine salt, baking powder and flour.
Gradually add dry mixture to creamed mixture.
Spread into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle a little granulated sugar over top.
Cool on rack.

title: corn casserole #1
directions: Saute green peppers and onion in margarine.
Combine with remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pack into 2 pie plates.
Freeze unbaked until ready to use.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: tangy grilled zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini lengthwise about 1/3-inch thick, creating long thick zucchini steaks.
Sprinkle both sides with lemon pepper and then with Parmesan cheese.
Grill first side on barbecue pit over hot flame.
Then baste with melted butter with garlic powder. Turn over and baste the other side.
Grill until light brown. Serve as vegetable dish; substitute for meat or on hamburger buns as a sandwich.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread marshmallows over bottom of pan.
Mix white cake as directed on box.
Combine dry jello and strawberries and pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Chop celery, onions and peppers.
Toss all together and let stand for 24 hours.

title: melt in your mouth sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the powdered sugar, white sugar and butter or margarine. Add vegetable oil, eggs and vanilla. Sift together, then add to the mixture the flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar. Chill dough. Form into balls and press with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Combine milk and flour in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring until it thickens and boils.
Let cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and cooled flour mixture.
Beat in electric mixer at medium speed until all ingredients are dissolved, about 10 minutes.
Frost cake; chill in refrigerator. More delicious if topped with your own chocolate icing, thinned to slow pouring consistency.
Enjoy.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Make a batter of the eggs with some salt and pepper.
Dip cubed pork in batter and brown in the oil.
Drain meat and add the bell pepper, garlic, salt, pineapple, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar and stock.
Thicken with cornstarch to desired consistency.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg until blended.
Beat in undrained pineapple and vanilla.
Combine oats, flour, orange peel, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat into pineapple mixture until blended.
Stir in raisins, coconut and walnuts.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of batter onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Each cookie contains 173 calories.

title: one pan turkey meal
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange broccoli crosswise in pan. Mix Bisquick, milk, egg and soup.
Beat 30 strokes with wire whisk.
Pour over broccoli in center of dish.
Sprinkle with turkey, cheese and pimento.
Bake until center is set, about 30 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in glass dish (approximately 9 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: orange frosting
directions: Cream butter and beat in orange juice and vanilla.
Gradually add the powdered sugar.
Add additional orange juice until it is spreading consistency.

title: pumpkin bundt
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Combine ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix on medium for 4 minutes. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out on cake plate.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or use drizzle icing.
Also good with Cool Whip on top.

title: apple bread
directions: Grease and flour a loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Mix 1 cup sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt until smooth.
Stir in apples and nuts. Spread in pan.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and the cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt in a small bowl. In a medium bowl, beat sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla together. Mix in dry ingredients.
Mix in chips.
Spread batter into greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes enough to serve 12.

title: lemon rounds
directions: Measure flour, soda and salt and sift.
Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg, lemon juice, rind and pecans. Sift in flour mixture, blending well.
Shape into 2 long rolls; wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Slice dough 1/4-inch thick. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until golden brown around edges.
Place on wire racks.
Cool completely.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in a tightly sealed container.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: pumpkin nut waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Beat egg yolks; combine with milk, butter and pumpkin. Add to dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour mixture onto hot waffle iron; sprinkle each waffle with 3 tablespoons pecans.
Bake until lightly browned (3 minutes).
Serve warm with maple syrup.
Yield: 8 (9-inch) waffles.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Break up lettuce in large container.
Slice onion over lettuce. Break the cauliflower into small pieces or slice.
Spread uncooked frozen peas.
Sprinkle cheese over next layer.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble over top.
Mix the mayonnaise with Hidden Valley Ranch salad seasoning; mix well.
Spread mayonnaise mixture carefully over entire top of salad.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly before serving.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Place cutting blade in food processor bowl.
Process eggs, a few tablespoons of the oil and remaining ingredients (except oil) until garlic cloves are completely chopped fine.
While machine is running, pour remaining oil through the feed tube in a slow, steady stream.
The longer the processor runs, the thicker the mayonnaise.

title: cherry pie cake
directions: Break up angel food cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make up vanilla pudding.
After you make pudding, add sour cream to pudding.
Put over cake.
Put cherry pie filling over vanilla pudding.
No cooking, just eat.

title: coffee sponge candy
directions: Dissolve coffee in vinegar in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add sugar and syrup.
Bring to a boil over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring to 300° or small amount separates into a hard brittle thread in cold water.
Remove from heat. Quickly stir in the soda, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Do not spread or it will not be spongy.
This will spread itself.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: chicken pot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine noodles, onion, chicken, carrots, green beans, peas, mushrooms, soup, salt and pepper.
Pour into an ungreased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle cheese and croutons on top and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: make ahead barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine ketchup, coffee, oil, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boil, uncovered.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soy sauce and sesame oil.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before using, warm to room temperature.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat margarine and applesauce until margarine is melted.
Mix dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Combine the two mixtures.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Remove from pan and cool 24 hours before slicing.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Spread on 3 layers of cake.

title: pat's hawaiian lemon pie(in honor of little applecart)
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together pineapple, brown sugar, the 1/4 cup coconut, and the 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix well. Spread pineapple mixture evenly over the bottom of the pastry shell.
Cover edge of pastry with foil.
Bake in a 425°
oven for 5 minutes.
Remove foil.
Continue baking about 10 minutes more or until golden.
Cool completely on a wire rack.

title: orange chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and 1/4 tsp. salt. Beat butter and shortening for 30 seconds; add sugars and beat till fluffy. Add egg, orange peel, orange juice and vanilla; beat well. Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating till well combined. Stir in chocolate. Shape into two 8-inch rolls. Wrap in waxed paper or clear plastic wrap; chill thoroughly. Cut into 1/4 -inch slices. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in 375 degree oven 10-12 minutes or until done. Makes about 60.

title: hungarian potato dish
directions: Coat 1 qt. baking dish with butter and dust sides and bottom with bread crumbs.
Layer sliced precooked potato and sliced eggs. Cover with 1/2 sour cream.
Dash with pepper, salt and 1 tsp. butter.
Repeat. Top with a sprinkling of paprika.

title: lemon wagon wheels
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Roll in balls and roll in powdered sugar. Bake 10 minutes at 325°.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Put rhubarb in the bottom of 9 x 13 pan; then layer with marshmallows. Sprinkle with sugar, then dry jello. Mix cake as directed on box and spread over top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes!

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix all dry
ingredients
together
until
it crumbles. Place in an oblong pan.
Bake
at 375° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Cook rice; saute onion, green pepper and celery in melted oleo until tender.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Grease a pie pan well.
Beat the egg whites real stiff.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Fold in pecans or walnuts and the cracker crumbs.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: roasted pacific woodchuck(traditional)
directions: Rub woodcocks inside and out with salt and candlefish oil. Roast over fire until tender inside but crisp outside.
As birds roast, add more oil and salt, brushed on with a green branch.

title: my mother's "glorified rice"
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Green grapes may be added, if desired.
Now fold creamy fruit mixture into chilled rice and serve.

title: aunt elsie's divinity
directions: Cook sugar and water to soft ball stage.
Pour over marshmallow cream in large bowl (not plastic).
Mix well.
Add nuts and salt.
Beat by hand until candy starts to lose gloss. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Cook in crock-pot 8 to 12 hours on low or 6 hours on high. Can be served with noodles or rice.

title: easy cheesy enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; pour off excess grease.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1/2 to 2/3 Velveeta cheese to ground beef until melted.
Lightly butter and warm tortillas.
Fill tortillas with ground beef mixture; roll and place in baking dish.
Melt remainder of Velveeta and sour cream and pour over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When cool, crumble 1/2 cake in punch bowl.
Mix pudding as directed.
When set, mix with Cool Whip. Pour 1/2 mixture over crumbled cake.
Spread half the pineapple on top.
Spread half the pie filling.
Sprinkle with 1/2 pecan pieces. Repeat the process, starting with other half of cake, put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: sweet and sour party sausage
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces and brown in oven in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Drain.
Combine cornstarch, vinegar and sugar in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix well all the ingredients listed in a large bowl.
Pour into 2 sprayed 13 x 9-inch pans or 1 large pan (such as a restaurant chaffer pan).
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Serves 65.

title: easy and good rolls
directions: In bowl mix the boiling water, sugar, margarine, salt and egg. In a separate glass bowl dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. Mix the contents of both bowls together and add 3 1/2 cups flour. Stir well with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Put in plastic bowl.
Cover with wax paper and a cloth.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, take out and make into rolls.
Cover and let dough rise about 2 hours or until very light.
Brush with melted butter and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crock pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in brine 14 days, using 3 cups non-iodized salt to 1 gallon of water.
Soak in stone jar (may use plastic bucket). Weight slices into liquid with plates or something heavy.
Wash, then soak overnight in alum water.
Rinse and soak 6 hours in vinegar.
Pour vinegar off and discard.
Add sugar and spices (tied in cheesecloth) to cucumbers.
Let stand.
Sugar will make enough liquid to cover pickles.
Stir occasionally with hand until sugar dissolves.
Pickles never need to be heated.
May be stored in stone jar or plastic bucket.
May remove a jar and refrigerate for crispness.

title: rice hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in skillet.
Set aside.
Mix soy sauce, mushroom soup and water together until smooth.
In casserole dish, mix together hamburger mixture, soup mixture and rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Be sure to stir at least every half an hour.
You may stir more, if needed.

title: kicked up mac and cheese
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 9 x 2 inch square baking dish with the butter. In a mixing bowl, whisk the eggs and milk together. Season the mixture with salt and pepper. Add 1 c. of the cheddar cheese, 1 c. of the white cheddar cheese, the hand and the tater tots. Mix the mixture thoroughly. Pour the mixture into the prepared pan and sprinkle the top with the remaining cheese. Place in the oven and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until the top is golden brown.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and red onions to desired size. Add Cheddar cheese and sunflower seeds.

title: spicy sausage & cheese rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
In a skillet cook and crumble sausage.
Add onion; cook until tender, drain. Stir in tomatoes and green chilies and chili powder.
Add rice and stir in cheese.

title: congealed chicken salad
directions: Add to broth; pour into mold and chill.
Can use a Bundt pan for mold.
When taken out of mold to serve, I put canned crab apples around it.

title: coconut chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
Set aside.

title: peppermint pattie brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, reserving patties and 2 cups of batter.
Put rest of batter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put patties on top of this, then add rest of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meats and add all other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Combine and fluff all ingredients, except for ice cream, then add ice cream.
Store in freezer.
Put 3 tablespoons mixer to 1 cup water; heat, add rum as desired.
Stir and top with whipped cream and cinnamon stick.

title: hawaiian spaghetti
directions: Simmer onion in oil until it turns yellow.
Take out onion and put in small bowl.
In another bowl, add hamburger, egg, salt, pepper and 3 teaspoons grated Parmesan cheese.
Mix together.
Make into balls, drop in oil and brown.
In a large pan, empty tomato juice, sugar, a little more salt and pepper, a little more Parmesan cheese and the garlic.
Add simmered onions and browned meat balls. Let simmer for about 1 hour.
Add catsup and pizza sauce.
Simmer for 1 more hour.
Makes enough sauce for 1 box of spaghetti.
(This sauce freezes well, also.)

title: vidalia onion and potato casserole
directions: Slice	potatoes
and	cook
in
water.
Drain.
Slice onions.
Layer
potatoes and onions in 10 x 13-inch glass dish sprayed
with
cooking
oil.
Pour	dressing over potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and bake 15 minutes at 350°, uncover and bake 10 minutes more to brown.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and beat eggs slightly.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into unbaked pie shell.
(Use your favorite pastry recipe.)
Bake at 325° until filling is firm.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolk and almond extract; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in 3 cups of coconut.
Cover tightly and chill until firm.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Butter a large baking pan. Process bread into fine crumbs.
Chop onion.
Cook onion in oil until soft, about 2 minutes.
Whisk eggs with milk, basil, salt and pepper.
Add spinach, onion, turkey, bread crumbs and lemon juice; mix well.
Turn mixture out into baking pan and form it into a 9 x 5-inch loaf.
Brush with ketchup and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Melt butter.
Baste loaf with butter and continue to bake, basting occasionally.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Have ready a baked and cooled 9-inch pastry shell.

title: salsa chicken and pasta
directions: You will need cooking spray.

title: deep fried pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and oil.
Stir in half of flour and mix well, then work in rest of flour.
Roll dough out in four 7-inch rounds, 1/8-inch thick.
Put fried bulk sausage, pizza sauce, mushrooms and cheese on each round.
Fold dough over and press edges real tight.
Deep fry in hot lard for 10 minutes on a side.
You may add different items, whatever you prefer on your pizza.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg together.
Add dry ingredients. Roll dough into small balls and dip top in water, then sugar. Bake on greased baking sheet about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except lettuce; toss gently.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue(depression style)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain excess grease off but not thoroughly. Add all other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes to an hour stirring occasionally.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Can make low-calorie by using fat free soups and light Velveeta.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix together apples with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Place 1/2 apple mixture on top of butter, pouring 1/2 sugar and cinnamon on them. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sweet noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into large, rectangular baking dish.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: one step old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients at low speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch square pan or Bundt pan and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook meat over medium heat just long enough to get redness out.
Add onions, garlic, bell pepper, celery, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer 3 hours.
Add tomato paste and sauce.
Simmer 1 hour longer.
Add pinch of oregano, sweet basil, rosemary and 1 small can mushrooms.
Freezes well.
When I make spaghetti sauce, I double the recipe, because it takes so long to cook.
I freeze it and use this sauce in my lasagna and spaghetti.
We like it.

title: eggplant stew
directions: Peel eggplant; put in 3-quart boiler.
Put 1 quart water in. Boil until tender; drain water off and chip up onion in the pot. Pour milk, margarine, black pepper and salt to suit taste.
Bring to boil about 10 minutes.
Put crackers in when ready to eat.

title: paul's easy chinese
directions: Dice pork sausage and hamburger; brown in frying pan.
Drain grease from pan.
Add water and beef granules to meat; season to taste.
Add vegetables; simmer until vegetables slightly crisp. Thicken mixture with cornstarch.
Make rice according to package directions.
Serve mixture over rice with chow mein noodles, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together in small bowl the cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Mix in a large bowl until thick the milk, pudding and vanilla.
Mix the ingredients together with Cool Whip.

title: tex-mex(dip)
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream with mayonnaise and taco mix.
Set aside.

title: spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl mix sugars with margarine.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir in flour.
Add nuts.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Spoon onto cookie sheet 2-inches apart with teaspoon.
Bake until slightly browned around edges (about 5 to 7 minutes).
Remove from sheet and place cookies on cooling rack.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: ardy allen's lemon chiffon pie
directions: Place in refrigerator for 45 minutes.
Mix juice and milk together. Whip cream; fold in.
Pour into shell.
Chill overnight.

title: sweet 'n sour sausages
directions: In saucepan, combine preserves, lemon juice, mustard and ginger.
Cook and stir until well blended.
Add frankfurters; heat thoroughly.
Serve hot with toothpicks.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cube stew beef or steak (size of dice).
In separate pan, add large can peeled tomatoes.
Add 1 small can tomato paste.
Add softened onion and peppers.
After browning meat, add to other ingredients.
Let simmer for a couple of hours after adding caraway seeds.
Peel and dice small potatoes and add to simmering ingredients.
When potatoes are soft, let simmer or serve the next day.
(Tastes better.)

title: potatoes moussaka *
directions: Layer potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or baking dish. Sprinkle with salt.
Set aside.

title: curried chicken
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until blended.
Drizzle mixture over about 2 1/2 pounds chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.

title: fresh corn salad
directions: Cook corn in enough water to cover 5 to 7 minutes; drain.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix oil, vinegar, lemon juice, parsley, sugar, salt (if desired), basil and cayenne pepper.
Cut cooled corn off the cob (should measure 4 cups).
Add corn, tomatoes, onion and peppers to oil mixture; mix well.
Cover and chill for several hours or overnight.
Yields 10 servings.

title: apricot pie
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 12-inch cake pan or 2 pie pans with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Melt oleo and sugar in a double boiler. Using a mixer, beat in eggs.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Pour over wafer crumbs.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Cool.
Place drained apricot halves over top.
Blanket with whipped cream.
Sprinkle top with more vanilla wafer crumbs.

title: lemon icebox cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers and cool.
Split layers to make 4 thin layers.
While cake is baking mix condensed milk and lemon juice between each layer.
Reserve 1/2 c. of mixture and mix with cool whip, frost top and sides of cake.
Store in refrigerator, covered.

title: texas taters
directions: Mix together all of the above except corn flakes and butter. Put in baking dish and top with corn flakes and butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Add all remaining ingredients except cheese and bake in greased dish at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with grated cheese and bake 5 minutes to melt.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and butter in pan.
Stir on medium heat until sugar dissolves and butter melts.
Boil until soft ball forms. Stir often.
Remove from heat; add rest of ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut before it becomes hard.

title: corney corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased, oblong casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: soft cream jumbles
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cinnamon together; set aside.

title: tomato bisque soup
directions: Mix together and heat in double boiler.
Makes 12 cups.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soups, salsa and milk.
In 9 x 13-inch pan make layer of tortillas, chicken mix and cheese.
Repeat.
End with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: b-4 breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage (drain well).
Beat eggs and add to milk.
Add salt, mustard and cheese.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 6 slices of bread.
Add sausage and egg mixture over bread.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: *Make this from 1 tablespoon salt, 1 teaspoon black pepper, 1/4 teaspoon paprika and 1/4 teaspoon garlic salt (not garlic powder).

title: daddy's broccoli salad
