directions: Chop broccoli and onion. Put in bowl with bacon bits and cheese. Stir together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Pour over salad.

title: chili-ham-cheese dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients and put into bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with bread cubes from the bread you have taken from loaf.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls in baking dish and bake.
Mix Hidden Valley ranch, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread over crust.
Spread vegetables over cheese mixture.
Top with cheese.

title: golden tea punch
directions: Brew tea for about 5 minutes, using tea bags and boiling water.
Remove tea bags and set aside.
To make sugar syrup, combine sugar and 1 cup water in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and set aside.

title: 24 hour pickles
directions: Wash and pack pickles in gallon jug.
Pour brine over pickles and let stand 24 hours.
Bring above mixture to a full boil. Place garlic cloves and dill in the jar.
Pour brine over pickles and tighten lid on jar.
Refrigerate jar after it is completely cooled.

title: galumphes(polish stuffed cabbage)
directions: Remove core of cabbage head and place head in boiling water until leaves are soft enough to remove one at a time without breaking. Mix hamburger with rice, egg, salt and pepper. Place small ball of hamburger mixture on center of a cabbage leaf and wrap it snugly. Place them in a small roasting pan that has been lined with the outside leaves from the head of cabbage. Fit them in close together. When all the galumphes are in pan, cover with more cabbage leaves. Pour vinegar mixture over them and place lid on tightly. Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours. Pour 1 can of tomato soup (right from the can) over the galumphes and return to oven for 30 minutes. Serve with mashed potatoes. (Sauce from galumphes is very good on the mashed potatoes.)

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix the pineapple, peanuts and apples. Set aside.
Bring to boil pineapple juice with the egg and add vinegar, flour and the sugar.
Boil until thick.
Cool slightly.
Pour over reserved ingredients.
Mix well, then add Cool Whip.
Cool overnight or all day before serving.

title: green bean relish salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep for 2 weeks.
Excellent!

title: "frozen" cucumbers
directions: Combine cucumbers, celery, peppers and onion.
Sprinkle over with salt and let stand 3 hours. Drain dry.
Combine remaining ingredients. When the sugar is dissolved in the cold vinegar, add drained-dry vegetables and spoon into containers.
These will keep 6 months in refrigerator and indefinitely in the freezer.

title: creamy onion dressing
directions: Mix ingredients. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: frata freeties(italian pancakes)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add other ingredients and mix; use a mixer.
Put in covered bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Heat griddle to 350° to 375° and oil surface.
Place dough by spoonfuls on surface and flatten so it will cook evenly.
Turn when brown. Serve with butter and sugar.
Recipe can be halved.

title: easy divinity fudge
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir together the sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook without stirring until temperature reaches 265° on a candy thermometer or until a small amount of syrup dropped into very cold water forms a ball that is hard enough to hold shape, yet plastic.

title: four cheese pate
directions: Beat 1 package of cream cheese with milk and sour cream until smooth.
Spread into a 9 inch pie plate lined with plastic wrap. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil 2 cups water, cinnamon and cloves for 5 minutes.
To this, add tea bags and boil for 4 minutes more.
Sift out solid particles.
Add sugar, lemon juice, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Add water to make 1/2 gallon.

title: french toast
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch dish.
Arrange bread in prepared dish. Pour mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
In separate bowl, mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Slowly add to butter mixture.
Mix in sour cream and 1/2 cup chips.
Put mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased, floured pan.
Sprinkle with rest of chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot spanish cheese dip
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions (omit salt). Drain thoroughly (reserve liquid, 1/2 cup).
Melt margarine; add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add reserved spinach liquid, milk and next 6 ingredients.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add spinach and mix.
Spoon into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs and 1 teaspoon melted margarine.
Sprinkle over spinach.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot over crackers or raw vegetable.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-O with water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in bowl to be served in.
Chill until firm.
Top with 1/2 Cool Whip.
Pour rest of mixture on Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator until serving time.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Let simmer 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package.
In pan, layer a row of noodles, meat sauce, spoonfuls of cottage cheese. Layer until used up.
Don't put noodles on top, they will dry out. Heat in oven at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in water and mix well. Knead dough until very elastic, about 10 minutes.
Divide dough into balls the size of small eggs.
Roll out each ball with a rolling pin into a very thin circle, about 7 or 8 inches in diameter, turning dough and rolling on both sides.
Cook or use as you would any flour tortilla.
Makes 16 to 20.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Skin and bone chicken.
Blend breadcrumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Melt butter; dip chicken in butter, then in breadcrumb mixture, coating thoroughly.
Roll each piece in firm roll; secure with toothpick. Put in baking dish. Squeeze lemon juice over chicken and any remaining butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.

title: white beans
directions: In a large pot, put in white beans and enough water to cover. Heat until the water comes to a boil.
Let stand for about 1 hour. Do not drain.
Put more water, oil, onions and meat seasoning. Let cook on medium fire for about 2 hours or 3 hours or until beans are creamy and tender.
Just before finished cooking, put in parsley.

title: macaroni-beef casserole
directions: Brown beef until clear.
Add onion, tomatoes, catsup, steak sauce and bell peppers.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni. Combine macaroni, parsley and beef mixture in baking dish.
Season to taste.
Spoon in mushroom soup and sprinkle grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen pickled cabbage
directions: Chop
cabbage
and
other vegetables very fine.
Can be put in blender to chop.
Add salt to mixture with enough water to cover. Let stand
for
hour.
Drain
well.
Combine and boil for 1 minute the sugar, vinegar, 1/4 cup water and celery seed.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix this and cabbage mixture together.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: banana-carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, banana and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in combined flour, baking powder, salt, soda and spices.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry in frying pan, using cooking oil.
Brown on both sides.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil the sugar, cocoa, butter and milk for 2 minutes, then add the peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased pan to cool and harden.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots on bias in 1-inch pieces.
Cook, covered, in boiling, salted water until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain. Combine next 4 items in small saucepan.
Add orange juice and cook, stirring all the time, until thick and bubbly.
Then boil 1 minute more and stir in oleo.
Pour over carrots and toss to coat.

title: chinese chicken and vegetables
directions: Heat 2 ounces of chicken broth in wok.
Add chicken strips and stir-fry until tender.
Remove chicken and put aside.
Add remaining broth to wok, heat and add vegetables.
Cook until tender.
Mix sauces and flavorings.
Add chicken to wok.
Pour in sauce mixture.
Stir-fry until entire dish is heated through. Serve with lots of steamed rice.

title: apple fritters
directions: Heat oil (2 or 3-inches deep).
Put about 1 cup chopped apples into fritter batter.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into oil.
Cook about 5 minutes.

title: lemon silk pie
directions: Fold Cool Whip into mixture of first three ingredients and put in your favorite pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with Cool Whip.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate.

title: carrot tsimmis
directions: Place all ingredients into large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Simmer over low heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
If mixture starts to become dry, add 1/2 cup of water at a time.
Cook until carrots are very soft but not mushy.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put sliced apples in a 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg together until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Drizzle butter over mixture. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 40 minutes.

title: spicy chicken chunks (low calorie)
directions: Put chicken in glass or plastic bowl.
Add hot sauce and stir lightly.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Mix flour with salt and spices.
Remove chicken from hot sauce; roll in flour mixture (using it up completely).
Heat oil in small skillet until HOT.
Fry the chicken chunks until they are cooked and crispy.

title: italian chicken with rice
directions: In a large skillet or electric frypan saute onion in olive oil.
Add chicken until lightly browned; drain.
Add cans of stewed tomatoes and zucchini and garlic powder.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat immediately and simmer 20 minutes.

title: lemon chiffon cake
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
While this is cooling, break eggs into mixing bowl; mix lightly and add salt.
Add oil, then add cooled jello followed by cake mix.
Beat thoroughly and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes (Be sure done).
While still hot, pierce cake all over with toothpick or fork.
Then pour over cake a mixture of 2 cups confectioners sugar and 1/2 cup lemon concentrate.
This will soak into cake and form glaze on top.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Toast noodles and almonds for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon apple crisp
directions: Coat a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with nonstick spray.
Add the apples.
In a large bowl, combine the oats, flour, raisins and cinnamon.
Drizzle with the apple juice, honey and oil.
Combine well.
Sprinkle over the fruit.
Bake at 350° until apples are hot and tender, 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: empanaditas
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add the vegetables and spices and let simmer.
When done, drain very well.
Roll the biscuits in circles. Place 1 spoonful of the meat mixture into the center and fold over making a half circle.
Press the edges with a fork making sure the biscuit is well sealed.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hungarian beef goulash
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat.
Brown meat and onion in cooking fat.
Pour off drippings.
Sprinkle paprika, marjoram and garlic over meat.
Add water; cover tightly and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes and tomato sauce and continue cooking for 30 minutes or until meat is done.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: Mix all together and press into 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage and boil for 10 minutes; drain well and pour into large bowl.
Mix next 4 ingredients together and stir into cabbage.
Combine last 3 ingredients and stir into cabbage mixture, then pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayo and seasoning salt together; stir in rest of ingredients and let set 1 hour or better the next day.

title: ooey gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg and pat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Butter dish and melt oleo. Combine rice and soup. Melt cheese. Add celery and onion. Stir in thawed broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Chill dough for 30 minutes or more.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 48 (1-inch) balls.
Place in lightly greased small muffin pans.
Shape the ball into a shell.
Bake for 12 minutes. Remove from oven and immediately press a miniature peanut butter cup into the hot crust.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Melt butter in microwave dish.
Drain pineapple juice.

Add juice, brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce to melted margarine. Stir. Add chicken. Cover with plastic wrap. Cook 9 minutes on High power. Turn chicken over. Cover and cook 8 minutes until well done. Remove chicken. Keep warm. Add water to liquid to make 2 cups.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water. Stir into cooking liquid. Cook 2 minutes on High. Add onions and pineapple.
Heat. Serve over chicken.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and melted margarine together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat sugar, margarine and vanilla until fluffy and spread.
Layer bananas over sugar mixture.
Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Drizzle chocolate syrup.
Garnish with cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: "fryd" green t'mators
directions: Wash your t-mators and slice them good-n-thin, about 1/8-inch thick.
Now get you a good, big bowl and add flour, salt, pepper and garlic; stir it up.
Now start adding your brew until it gets nice and thick, sort of like good gravy!
Put cooking oil in a large skillet and get it good and hot.
Dip your mators in batter. Put them in skillet and fry them golden brown.
Lay them on a paper towel and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Eat them while they're hot.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine eggs, sugar, margarine, vanilla and lemon juice. Stir in coconut and pecans. Pour into pie shell and bake for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg with fork; fold in milk and oil.
Blend dry ingredients; stir in just until flour is moistened.
Fold blueberries gently into mixture.
Fill greased muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Cook at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with
fork.
Add
sugar
and syrup, then salt and vanilla.
Last the melted butter.
Place the pecans in the bottom of an
unbaked pie crust.
Add the filling.
The pecans will rise to the top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: cherry pineapple delight
directions: Spread pie filling in buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour pineapple over pie filling and sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour oleo over cake mix and then top with pecan pieces.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: scrambled eggs(huevos revueltos)
directions: Saute onion, garlic and chiles in tomato sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 4 minutes.
Add eggs.
Stir.
Serve immediately.

title: beer soup
directions: Add water to beer; let come to a boil.
Season with salt and nutmeg, if desired.
Beat yolks well with a little sugar and flour, mixed; add milk.
Stir until smooth.
Stir all together in the hot beer mixture; let come nearly to a boil.
Fold in beaten whites and serve at once with toasted bread cubes.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Use firm, crisp apples.
If apples lack tartness, use an additional 1/4 cup of lemon juice for each 6 quarts.
Wash, peel and core apples.
Slice apples 1/2 inch thick and place in water containing 1 teaspoon of ascorbic acid crystals or 6 (500 mg) vitamin C tablets in 1 gallon of water to prevent browning.
Place 6 cups at a time in 1 gallon boiling water.
Boil each batch 1 minute after water returns to a boil.
Keep in a covered pot so they will stay warm.
Combine sugar, clear jel A, cinnamon and nutmeg in large kettle with water and apple juice.
Stir and cook on medium-high heat until mixture thickens and begins to bubble. Drain apple slices.
Add lemon juice and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Fold in apple slices, immediately fill jars and process without delay.
Process in boiling water canner 30 minutes for pints or quarts.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add margarine and beat. Add dry ingredients.
Pour into 8-inch square greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: extra moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, add water last.
Bake at 350° in well-greased rectangular pan, 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion in a skillet. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine.
Cook in a 275° oven for 5 hours.

title: butterscotch chews
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Mix nuts with noodles into melted chips and drop on waxed paper.
Makes about 30.

title: four layer cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, butter, salt and pecans and pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or dish. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Crust will not turn brown. Let cool before adding Second Layer.

title: strawberry kringle cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; cool.
Add sour cream, sugar and strawberries.
Refrigerate overnight.
Split cake layers to make 4 layers.
Put strawberry filling between layers and on top.
Put in sealed container and refrigerate 24 hours.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: cream mustard sauce
directions: Beat whipping cream in chilled 1 1/2-pint bowl until stiff. Mix remaining ingredients.
Fold into whipped cream.
Makes about 1 cup sauce; 25 calories per tablespoon.

title: turtles
directions: Place foil on a baking sheet, then 1 layer pretzels. Put 1 Rolo on each pretzel. Place in oven at 250° for 4 minutes. Take out of oven. Place 1 half pecan on each one and press down. Let cool before taking off foil.

title: squash au gratin
directions: Combine squash, melted butter or margarine, seasoning and beaten eggs.
Alternate layers of squash, bread crumbs and cheese in 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: amish corn dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix milk and sugar and bring to a boil.
Mix last 5 items well and add to boiled mixture.
Place teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Refrigerate until hard.

title: chili meat balls
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt, egg and tomato soup. Shape into 2-inch meat balls.
Brown in 1 tablespoon of shortening.
Mix remaining soup, chili powder and water.
Pour over meat balls.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: a meal-in-one casserole
directions: Place meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Thinly slice onion and pepper and place on top of meat.
Spread undiluted soup on top of pepper.
Add potato tots to cover top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Mix jello according to package, then add strawberries.
Mix vanilla pudding according to directions, then add Cool Whip.
Layer in large bowl: cake, jello, pudding, cake, jello and pudding.
Chill well before serving.

title: barbecue raccoon
directions: Boil coon, onion and potatoes for 1 1/2 hours.
Debone.
Mix with barbecue sauce and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Save skin for Daniel Boone hat or car antenna.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, water and oil.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Fold in strawberries, pour into greased and lightly floured cake pans and bake at 325° until done (about 25 minutes).

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat egg whites in medium bowl on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Beat remaining ingredients, except frosting and 2 cups coconut in large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured round pans, 8 x 1 1/2-inch.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool cake completely.

title: banana pineapple cool whip salad
directions: Make pudding (following directions on side of package).
Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
One and one-half cups walnuts can be added to make this dessert even better.

title: joe froggers yankee magazine cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; stir in molasses and rum.
Add all dry ingredients and chill over night.
Roll in balls the size of a walnut.
(Roll in sugar.)
Heat oven to 350°.
Use a greased cookie sheet; bake time will depend on thickness, (10 minutes).
Yield about 5 dozen.
Good.

title: breakfast casserole by mavis
directions: Put buttered bread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
"Pam" should be sprayed on the pan ahead of time preferably.
Top bread with sausage and cover with cheese.
Peppers and/or onions may be added somewhere in this process.
Let stand overnight.
The next day, cook at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cheesecake delight(no bake)
directions: Make day before needed.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump first 3 ingredients into 13 x 9-inch baking dish in order and carefully spread each layer.
Slice margarine sticks and make sure they cover the dry cake mix.
Put into 350° oven and bake for 1 hour.
Great cobbler dessert.

title: christmas almond creme(6 servings)
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over water.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until completely dissolved.
In blender or processor, process cream, sugar, eggs and almond extract 2 minutes.
While processing, gradually add gelatine mixture and process until blended.
Pour into dessert dishes and chill. Garnish with strawberries or other fruit or whipped cream and sliced, toasted almonds.

title: guacamole meat dish
directions: Cook ground beef, hot sausage, large onion and salt until brown, then drain.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan with refried beans. Add meat mixture.
Spread with green chilies.
Cover with Cheddar and Monterey Jack.
Spread with taco sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Mix sour cream and avocado dip.
Spread on hot mixture. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped green onions.
Serve with chips to dip.

title: hot fudge brownies
directions: Bake brownies as per directions on box.
You might want to add some of the crushed nuts to the brownie mix.
Take the jar of hot fudge and place jar in a saucepan full of water.
Set it on a stove to get the fudge hot.
Or, place jar in a microwave oven.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Estimate on amount of maraschino cherries.
Drain fruit. Make glaze using pudding mix, lemon juice and reserved pineapple juice. Fold fruits into above mixture.
It is ready to serve.
It will keep in the refrigerator for many days.
Can be made the night before serving.

title: cherry confetti cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Cream shortening. Gradually add sugar.
Cream well.
Add extract and eggs, one at a time.
Beat one minute.
Measure milk.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, ending with dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly with each addition.
Add nuts.
Add cherries to the batter.
Bake at 350° in prepared Bundt pan for 65 minutes.
When done, spread with cinnamon, butter and sugar.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail and glaze in a serving bowl.
Top with Cool Whip.
Delicious and easy.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish; combine sour cream and chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix crumbled Ritz crackers with melted margarine and poppy seed.
Spread cracker mixture over chicken. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken.
When done, debone.
Mix chicken with cream of chicken, onions, chili and sour cream.
Add spices to taste.
Layer tortillas on bottom of pan, covering it.
Add ingredients in layers.
Sprinkle cheese over it.
Layer again with tortillas, etc. Add rest of cheese on top of last layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugars until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla extract; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients thoroughly and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the last 2 ingredients and put on top of cake. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Great served with whipped topping.

title: easy cookies
directions: Shape into balls.
Roll each in powdered sugar.
Bake at 325°. Great for a shower or tea.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in dish as bottom layer. Mix cheese and salsa together. Cook in oven at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve with scoop tacos.

title: lime mist
directions: Combine
jello	and
applesauce in saucepan.
Heat until jello is
dissolved,
cool.
Stir in celery, nuts and cherries (cut up)
and
the
lemon-lime
beverage.
Chill until syrupy. Fold Cool
Whip	into cooled jello mixture.
Add a few drops of green food
coloring if you like.
Pour into 2 quart container and let firm up.
Do not freeze.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: taco squares
directions: Mix Bisquick and press into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread up the sides as well.
Brown hamburger; drain and stir in taco seasoning.
Pour into pan.
Make layers over the hamburger.
First the tomatoes, then chiles and then the avocado slices.
Mix together the mayonnaise, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Pour over top of layers.
Sprinkle top with sliced olives and paprika.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake an additional 10 minutes to lightly brown the top.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage or bacon and drain.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish and spread bread cubes evenly over bottom.
Crumble sausage or bacon over bread.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt together and pour over sausage or bacon.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: light and easy lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil; drain.
Combine soups and milk; stir in lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken and top with lemon slice.
Reduce heat and simmer until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
(Preparation time: 5 minutes.
Cooking time: 15 minutes.)
Serves 4.

title: creative clay
directions: Mix soda and cornstarch together; add water.
Cook and stir over low heat until consistency of mashed potatoes.
Remove from heat and cover with damp cloth until cool enough to handle.
Use for Play Dough or jewelry shaping or roll it out to make ornamental cookies.
Clay dries very hard.
Store in plastic bag to keep from drying out.
Clay may be colored with food coloring added to the water or painted with tempera when dry.

title: boneless deer meat with gravy
directions: Place two tablespoons of oil in Dutch oven or large pot with lid.
Heat over medium-high temperature.
Pound meat with mallet using facet side.
Sprinkle flour on both sides of meat lightly. Brown meat on both sides, adding oil as needed.
Add beer, rosemary, seasoned	salt
and
black
pepper.
Simmer 45 minutes. Add onions	and green pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until done.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Debone chicken.
Mix all ingredients together and cook slow for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: Saute bacon until crisp; remove bacon and reserve.
Saute onion in drippings until lightly browned.
Add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper; heat to boiling.
Add potatoes, parsley and bacon; heat thoroughly and serve immediately.
Serves 4 generously.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Thaw potatoes between layers of paper towels to remove excess moisture. Press potatoes into bottom and up sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate. Drizzle with butter.

title: long grain and wild rice casserole
directions: In a large, heavy pot, brown sausage.
Drain grease in a colander.
In the same pot, saute celery, onion, bell pepper and garlic in small amount of chicken broth.
Add remaining chicken broth and the drained sausage.
To this, add mushroom soup, celery soup, drained water chestnuts and mushrooms; stir well.
Add rice, enclosed herb packet and almonds.
Pour into a 16 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butter sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add egg yolks to whites, one at a time, beating continuously, then add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Stir until flour is absorbed.
Heat milk to boiling point; add butter and let melt.
Add milk and butter mixture all at once to batter; continue mixing until well blended. Pour into 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ming's cashew chicken
directions: Bone and skin chicken.
If necessary, slice wafer thin and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Mix in 1 tablespoon oil and 1 teaspoon cornstarch thoroughly.
Saute nuts in 1 tablespoon oil until slightly brown.
In hot pan, place 3 tablespoons oil and salt. Add chicken and saute on hot fire until meat is done.
Add stock, mushrooms, shoots and peas.
Cover and cook 1 minute before adding sugar, soy sauce and cornstarch mixed with water.
Stir until thick.
Pour in nuts.
Mix slightly.
Serve with rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Add lemon juice to mashed bananas and stir into creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients and add with nuts to mixture, stirring only enough to mix thoroughly.
Pour into two small, well-greased bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done to toothpick test.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: sweet potato boats
directions: Bake sweet potatoes at 375° for 60 minutes.
With a sharp knife, cut a lengthwise oval in peel; scoop out the centers, leaving 1/4-inch shells.
Place potato centers in a medium size mixing bowl with 1/2 cup cheese, milk, butter, salt and pepper. Whip and stuff back into shells.
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika.

title: energy drink
directions: Blend in blender and drink.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning in 13 x 9-inch pan and chill.
Spread on one jar of picante sauce.
Top with green olives, green onions, lettuce and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.

title: appetizer
directions: Spread cream cheese on beef slices.
Place 1 green onion on cream cheese and roll up.

title: macadamia chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix together butter and brown sugar until creamy. Add egg and vanilla. Beat until light. Blend in flour, baking soda, chips and nuts.
Mix until well blended. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until firm.
Do not overbake.

title: goofy cake
directions: Sift into ungreased pan.
Pour over all 1 cup cold water.
Mix thoroughly with fork.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 small cake.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients on stove; boil 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Place in mixer bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop on waxed paper until set.

title: scalloped cheese tomatoes
directions: Place
layer
of
stuffing
in
buttered shallow baking dish. To the tomatoes add
butter, drippings, salt and sugar. Cover stuffing with tomato, then
layer of cheese, then onion. Repeat ending with cheese on
top.
Sprinkle
with oregano and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix
all
together and place in refrigerator overnight. Put in greased muffin pans and bake.
No rising.
Will keep in refrigerator to use as needed.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Peel and cube the potatoes. Add salt and pepper and minced garlic and cook until done. Drain. Add the mayonnaise, eggs, mustard, salad dressing and salt and pepper to taste. Mix all together. Serve warm.

title: deluxe pumpkin custards
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, pumpkin, cream, brown sugar, pumpkin pie spice and salt until smooth.
Pour into a six 6 ounce custard cup.
Place cups in baking pan, 15 x 9 x 2-inch.
Pour very hot water into pan to within 1/2-inch of the top of the cups. Bake 20 minutes.
Prepare Crunchy Topping.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening.
Add water and mix well.
Add vinegar and egg; mix well.
It's ready to use or let set in refrigerator until cold.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days or roll out and put in pans and freeze.

title: popcorn wreath
directions: In medium saucepan, melt caramels, margarine, oil and marshmallows, stirring constantly.
In large bowl, combine popcorn and peanuts.
Add caramel mixture and mix well.
Add M&M's.
Press into lightly oiled Bundt pan.
Remove when cool.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: In medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, spinach, egg product and Italian seasoning; set aside.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer 1/3 each of noodles, spinach filling and remaining sauce; repeat twice. Sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 375°.
Uncover; bake 25 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sweet style corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease pan well; bake 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple basket salad
directions: Cut pineapple into halves lengthwise and scoop out the pulp in cubes or balls.
Mix with fruit salad and pile in pineapple basket.
Serve with mayonnaise.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, peas and celery in broth until tender. Cool.
Put in blender, cover and cream on high speed until mixture is perfectly smooth.
Add cream and blend at low speed until thoroughly mixed.
Serve icy cold topped with chopped chives.

title: light and creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, pie filling mix and pumpkin pie spice in mixer bowl. Beat at lowest speed until well combined, about 1 minute. Fold in 2 1/2 cups of Cool Whip. Spoon into crust and freeze until firm, about 4 hours. Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Place 1/3 of the tortillas in a greased casserole.
Cover with 1/3 of the chicken, chilies and cheese.
Repeat layers 2 times. Spread soup over top layer.
Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until heated through.
May be prepared a day in advance and refrigerated until ready to bake.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Add meal and flour.
Mix with buttermilk until texture is like creamed potatoes.
Drop from teaspoon into deep fryer.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Start with cold oven.
Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each one.
Add flour (2 cups), alternating with milk.
Sift remaining flour with baking powder and salt; add to mixture, then add lemon flavoring.
Pour into large tube pan.
Put into cold oven; set temperature at 350°. Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: waffles
directions: Beat ingredients with wire whisk or hand beater until well blended.
Pour onto center of hot waffle iron. Bake until steaming stops. Remove carefully. Makes six 9-inch waffles.

title: sour milk pancakes and syrup
directions: Beat all ingredients.
Makes about 18 cakes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and shortening real good.
Add eggs; mix until smooth.
Add baking powder, salt and cocoa and stir.
Then add flour and milk intermittently.
Blend with mixer.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in
Bundt pan.

title: oriental baked pork or beef roast
directions: Trim outside fat off meat if necessary to 1/4-inch cover.
Cut 1/2-inch deep slits in top about every inch so marinate can soak in.

title: coq au "beer"
directions: Brown chicken in skillet over medium heat in a small amount of oil.
After turning once, add the onion that has been sliced thin.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, paprika and garlic.
When brown, add the beer; cover and reduce heat to low.
Simmer about one-half hour.
Serve with rice.

title: apple-date smoothie
directions: Whirl all the ingredients in a blender until smooth. Add ice, if you wish.

title: herbed drumsticks
directions: Wash and dry the drumsticks.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Dip chicken in the melted butter, then roll in crumbs.
Arrange chicken, skin side up, on greased baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining butter and crumbs over chicken.
Bake at 375° for about an hour. Do not turn chicken.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Melt butter; mix in crumbs.
Beat together milk and Dream Whip.
Beat cheese until smooth and add sugar and vanilla.
Beat a little longer (cheese should be room temperature).
Add to Dream Whip.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and jello until well blended.
Add pineapple and oranges; mix well.
Pour into dish and chill.

title: muffins(with master mix)
directions: Mix water and egg.
Blend with dry ingredients.
Bake in muffin pan lined with baking paper cups at 425° for 25 minutes. Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare and slice apples and put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been buttered.
Mix together the flour and brown sugar. Cut in the butter and spread over apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ham salad hors d'oeuvres
directions: Put ham in food processor or blender. Combine remaining ingredients with ham. Add pepper to taste.
Serve on crackers or mini rye bread.

title: grits and cheese casserole
directions: Stir grits into boiling water and add salt.
Return to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, cheese and hot sauce, stirring until butter and cheese melt.

title: mom's broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients except onions and season to taste.
Put in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with Durkee onions and cook for 5 more minutes.
